Sprint across the savannah with a cheetah, plunge into the ocean with a seal, and swing through the trees with a chimp!

title: Ned Kelly
description: In this rousing, fact-based tale of the Australian frontier, Mick Jagger makes his screen debut as a notorious outlaw who heads a band of Irish gunslingers as they try to outrun British authorities.

title: No Knock List
description: When two hardened criminals make a break from prison, they hatch their plan to rob a paranoid recluse who runs a boarding house in her sprawling Victorian manor. As their plan seems to be coming together, things inside begin to unravel.

title: No Way to Live
description: In the 1950s American South, an interracial teenage couple rob and steal to escape their oppressive town, but when violence erupts they are forced to confront their own dark secrets.

title: Paranormal Prison
description: The impending demolition of an abandoned prison has the paranormal investigation team rushed to spend a night within the prison's walls, recording everything hoping to capture elusive spirits.

title: Pretty Ugly People
description: A woman lures her group of old college friends to the Montana wilderness to help celebrate her new self.

title: Racing With The Moon
description: On the brink of adulthood in a small-town, teens Henry and Nicky try to have a last hurrah before joining the Marines in World War II. But when Henry falls in love with a newcomer and Nicky gets in trouble, they find themselves in a grown-up world.

title: Samrat Prithviraj
description: Set in 12th Century India, a glorious retelling of life of Samrat Prithviraj Chauhan (Akshay Kumar), one of India’s greatest emperors. Known for his bravery, and sacrifice for the nation as much as for his immortal love story with Princess Sanyogita (Manushi Chhillar), Samrat Prithviraj Chauhan took on the mighty Mohammed Ghori (Manav Vij) of Ghazni, deflating his plans of capturing India.

title: Say Your Prayers
description: Two orphaned brothers turned radical Christian hitmen venture to a rural town to assassinate a famed atheist writer.

title: Seabiscuit
description: True story of the undersized Depression-era racehorse whose victories lifted not only the spirits of the team behind it but also those of the nation as well.

title: Sherlock Holmes: The Secret Weapon
description: Sherlock Holmes and Doctor Watson must protect a Swiss inventor of an advanced bomb sight from falling into German hands.

title: Ski Patrol
description: The fun-loving guys of the ski patrol must outsmart an obnoxious group of ski instructors hired by a developer to sabotage and create havoc in a wacky ski resort. From the producer of the "Police Academy" series.

title: Slash
description: Teenage Neil is exploring his sexuality by writing same-sex, erotic fan fiction about a popular sci-fi character. When he discovers Julia is also questioning who she is, they go on an adventure of self discovery through their passion for writing.

title: Son of God
description: From producers Mark Burnett and Roma Downey, Son of God brings the powerful and inspirational story of Jesus to life for a whole new generation of families to enjoy.

title: Speed
description: An L.A. cop (Keanu Reeves) trapped on a runaway city bus set to explode if it falls under 50 mph must help one of the terrified passengers (Sandra Bullock) steer the bus to safety!

title: Stay
description: A woman finds out she's pregnant and returns home when the expectant father wants nothing to do with her.

title: Stuff
description: A married lesbian couple are in a rut and seem to be going through the motions of a life together but excitement comes in the guise of a single tattooed mother with a shady past and proves to be more temptation than the couples' marriage can handle.

title: The Fighter
description: Based on the story of Micky Ward, a fledgling boxer tries to escape the shadow of his more famous, but troubled, older boxing brother and get his own shot at greatness.

title: The Four Feathers
description: Heath Ledger stars as Harry Feversham, a British soldier with a golden future - until he inexplicably resigns from his regiment. Harry is branded a coward, disowned by his family, his beautiful fiancee and his best friend.

title: The Games Maker
description: Young Ivan's newfound love of board games catapults him into the fantastical and competitive world of game invention. But when an evil games master attempts to destroy the world Ivan's grandfather created, he must rise up against his nemesis and risk losing everything to win the game.

title: The Gospel According to André
description: This intimate portrait for André Leon Tally, a fixture in the world of fashion, takes viewers on a journey from André’s roots growing up to becoming one of the most influential tastemakers and fashion curators of our times.

title: The Honor Farm
description: Several students attend a psychedelic party in the woods on prom night and are forever changed.

title: The Hunted
description: Tommy Lee Jones and Benicio del Toro star in this taut action thriller about a renegade assassin pursued through the Pacific Northwest wilderness by the survival expert who trained him.

title: The Italian Job
description: Charlie Croker pulled off the crime of a lifetime. The one thing that he didn't plan on was being double-crossed. Now he wants more than the job's payoff...he wants payback. Along with a drop-dead gorgeous safecracker Croker and his team take off to re-steal the loot and end up in a pulse-pounding, pedal-to-the-metal chase that careens up, down, above and below the streets of Los Angeles.

title: The Pirates! Band Of Misfits
description: A group of pirates journey to London and meet Charles Darwin, a talking chimp named Mister Bobo and an enemy looking to wipe them out. Based on "The Pirates! (In an Adventure With Scientists)," the best-selling books by Gideon Defoe.

title: The Price
description: Secrets threaten to destroy a young Nigerian-American while he navigates complications in family, love, and business in the cutthroat world of Wall Street.

title: The Republic of Two
description: After twentysomethings Tim and Caroline decide to move in together, they struggle with the changes in their relationship that cohabitation brings.

title: The Rest of Us
description: A divorced mother and her daughter must contend with living in the same house as the ex-husband's second wife and daughter following his unexpected death.

title: The Sky Pilot
description: The sky pilot is a preacher who helps Gwen walk again after a near-fatal accident.

title: The Twin
description: Jocelyn’s boyfriend is perfect, except for his dangerous identical twin brother, Derek, who just escaped from a mental institution. When Derek unspools a twisted plan of revenge with Jocelyn in his crosshairs, her mother Ashley must act fast before her daughter falls victim to a psychopath.

title: Thomas Rhett: The Live Experience
description: Join superstar Thomas Rhett for a live concert event celebrating the release of his sixth studio album, Where We Started.

title: Throw Momma from the Train
description: A bitter professor who wants his ex-wife dead and one of his students with an over-bearing mother contemplate exchanging murders-but will they actually go through with it?...

title: VERY CAVALLARI
description: Season 3 of Very Cavallari features long-time celebrity, businesswoman, wife and mother, Kristin Cavallari as she balances it all with husband, Jay Cutler by her side.

title: Waiting for the Barbarians
description: The Magistrate of an isolated frontier settlement on the border of an unnamed empire looks forward to an easy retirement until the arrival of Colonel Roll, whose task it is to report on the activities of the 'barbarians' and on the security situation on the border. Joll conducts a series of ruthless interrogations, which leads the Magistrate to question his loyalty to the empire.

title: Will Penny
description: Will has two problems to deal with: he's in love with another man's wife, and the outlaw gang is on its way back to finish him off...

title: Witness For The Prosecution
description: When a wealthy widow is murdered, her married suitor (Tyrone Power) is accused of the crime. His only hope for acquittal is the testimony of his wife (Marlene Dietrich) but his alibi shatters when she reveals some shocking secrets of her own!

title: Yellowbeard
description: A spoof swashbuckler in which a villainous pirate makes an effort to locate a treasure he buried years earlier.

title: Yentl
description: Based on a short story, "Yentl, the Yeshiva Boy," by Isaac Bashevis Singer. Yentl is the story of a young Eastern European woman, who, very early in our century (pre-WWI), disguises herself as a boy in order to pursue her passion for studying the Torah. Yentl (Streisand) has no trouble passing for a boy as she pursues her studies, but when she falls in love with a fellow student (Mandy Patinkin) she cannot, of course, express her feelings. Circumstances of Jewish law force the "boy" Yentl to marry a girl (Amy Irving), but the concealment must continue and Yentl must invent reasons for a long-delayed "consumation" of the marriage. Finally, she reveals her secret to her bride, who, after a time of shock, accepts Yentl for what she is.

title: A Bucket of Blood
description: A black comedy by writer Charles B. Griffith and director Roger Corman. Walter (Dick Miller) kicks off an unlikely art career when he kills a cat and hides the evidence with plaster. His "sculptures" earn artistic clout; then people start to disappear.

title: American Gangster: Trap Queens
description: Trap Queens is a new installment of the critically acclaimed American Gangster series that examines the lives and the legend behind some of America's most notorious female criminals.

title: Ana
description: Ana fue criada para ser famosa y bella pero descubre que su vida ha sido regida por las apariencias. Esta es la historia de una adolescencia tardía de quien no tiene miedo de perderse para encontrarse

title: Approaching The Unknown
description: As the world watches Captain William D. Stanaforth (Mark Strong) on a solo mission to Mars, he must delve into the darkest places of his mind and outer space to guide a failing ship to the surface of Mars.

title: Atlantic City
description: In a corrupt city, a small-time gangster and estranged wife of a pot dealer find themselves thrown together in an escapade of love, money, drugs, and danger.

title: Below the Surface
description: In a hostage situation that changes Denmark forever, 15 Danes have their lives upended when the Metro train they are travelling on is hijacked. Politicians argue whether to negotiate with terrorists; ordinary Danes wonder if it could just as easily have been them. And among the hostages one thought is shared by all: “Am I going to die now?” From Walter Presents, in Danish with English subtitles.

title: Bonanza
description: *Season 1 included with Prime until 5/31*. Adam saves a White woman about to be killed by some Indians that believe she is a mountain spirit. He kills the men, but is wounded. The woman nurses him back to health, while the rest of the tribe is still looking for her. Starring: Lorne Greene, Pernell Roberts, Michael Landon

title: Camp Lazlo
description: N/A

title: Carnival Story
description: An American carnival in Germany sets the scene for sin, sex and melodrama.

title: Christine Jorgensen Story
description: The true story of the first sex-change operation which changed "George" into "Christine" in 1950s Denmark.

title: Clip: A2D8S
description: A2D8S

title: Corpse Vanishes
description: A scientist extracts gland fluid to keep wife young.

title: Cosmo Jones, Crime Smasher
description: An amateur detective and a janitor try to find a kidnapped heiress.

title: D.O.A.
description: A man is told he has only a week to live after doctors found he is suffering from a deadly luminous toxin with no antidote. Thus begins his quest to find who poisoned him.

title: Dynamite Warrior
description: After seeing his parents viciously murdered by a mysterious, tattoo-covered killer.

title: Five Little Babies Nursery Rhymes & Kids Songs - Baby Toot Toot
description: Enjoy Baby Toot Toot popular easy to learn nursery rhymes for babies and toddlers, which the children love to sing and dance along with. Learn these kids songs and new words at the same time. Learn about Twinkle Twinkle Little Star, Five Little Monkeys, Finger Family and more made easy and fun with this preschool playlist.

title: Five Little Ducklings + More Nursery Rhymes & Kids Songs - Farmees
description: Let's groove to the Five Little Ducklings !! Kids songs and nursery rhymes that the little ones will love. Come join Farmees as they sing along and dance to these kids rhymes like Tractor on The Wheels, Humpty Dumpty, Bath Song, Five Little Cows and many more baby songs.

title: Follow the Money
description: When a body is found near a wind farm, the investigation leads detective Mads to Denmark’s leading energy company, Energreen. Peek into the dark side of an industry, where clean energy is a dirty business. Originally aired in Denmark as “Bedrag.”

title: Forensic Factor
description: Based on true crimes solved by an elite team of investigators, "Forensic Factor" details the trade secrets used by the world's best sleuths to nab the most elusive criminals.

title: Get Big
description: "Get Big" follows the misadventures of two friends, Alec and Nate, as they reconnect to attend a high school classmate's wedding.

title: Guerrilla: The Taking of Patty Hearst
description: The Symbionese Liberation Army (SLA). The SLA wreaked havoc on the West Coast and our national psyche, leaving behind a rich trove of paranoid recordings and scores of violent acts, including the kidnapping of heiress Patty Hearst who would subsequently join the SLA under the alias "Tania."

title: Hot Wheels City
description: In a world of wheels, all tracks lead to Hot Wheels City, a full-throttle metropolis that never hits the breaks, where overpasses loop through the bridge and tunnel landscape. But don't get caught off guard, this city isn't as safe as it seems.

title: Hotel Colonial
description: Marco Veniera goes to Bogota, Columbia to find his brother, Luca who supposedly committed suicide. In his search, he meets fiery and exotic Irene Costa, who leads him into the depths of the Amazon jungle.

title: How The States Got Their Shapes
description: Every line on the map tells a different story.

title: I'll Be Home for Christmas
description: Jackie Foster has the perfect life until her dad Jack returns home and reluctantly agrees to spend Christmas with her and her daughter Gracie. Stars James Brolin, Mena Suvari and Giselle Eisenberg.

title: Investiture of the Gods
description: The story is set in the era of the decline of the Shang dynasty (1600-1046 BC) and the rise of the Zhou dynasty (1046-256 BC). It intertwines numerous elements of Chinese mythology, including deities, immortals and spirits.

title: Jive Turkey
description: Italian mobsters go tooth and nail with black gangsters in Harlem in this Blaxploitation era flick, originally released as Baby Needs a New Pair of Shoes. Frank DeKova stars as Big Tony, head of the Italian faction.

title: Johny Johny Yes Papa + More Sing Along Songs for Babies - Boom Buddies
description: Sing & Dance along to Johny Johny Yes Papa! Enjoy popular easy to learn kids songs for babies and toddlers. Boom Buddies Nursery Rhyme is a kids tv show where you can learn baby songs like Finger Family, Are You Sleeping Brother John, Ice Cream song, Colors song and many more children songs.

title: Kentucky Rifle
description: A man escorts a wagon load of Kentucky rifles through Indian territory and must find a way to get through without losing the rifles to the Indians.

title: Labuntina
description: Sing along with Lili, Judi and Kodi and learn about numbers, ABC, animals, and much more!

title: Lidia Celebrates America
description: From PBS: Celebrate culture with Lidia Bastianich.

title: Magic Stocking
description: Lindsey, a single mom, is closed off to life after losing her husband a few years back. When she buys a stocking at her town's Christmas craft fair, the family begins "magically" finding items in the stocking.

title: Max Steel: The Wrath of Makino
description: Makino, devourer of worlds, is back! How can this be? He was blasted to bits high in orbit above earth by Max Steel. But Makino's evil heart beats on calling upon his remaining UltraLinks to become his heir and claim his power. The overlord's spirit shall possess whoever touches his heart first, with Max racing to stop them! Will Max's new Turbo Nova mode be enough to defeat a Makino reborn?

title: Milton Berle Show
description: The second incarnation of 'Mr. Television' Milton Berle's variety TV series.

title: Mr. D
description: In the final season, Gerry takes on a whole new surprising role to the dismay of the other staff.

title: My Dear Secretary
description: A secretary who is an aspiring writer is hired by a well known novelist to be his secretary. She did not realize she would be working at his apartment and have to endure all his guests and his roommate.

title: One Last Thing
description: A young man with a terminal illness makes an unconventional request on local television.

title: Popeye
description: The adventures of the famous sailor man, Popeye (Robbin Williams), and his friends in the seaside town of Sweethaven.

title: Pororo Car Songs
description: Friends who interested in cars are gather here! Let's sing along the Pororo Car Songs!

title: Public Cowboy No. 1
description: Rustlers using modern technology (airplanes, shortwave radios, refrigerated trucks) are Gene's target.

title: Racing with the Moon
description: Henry "Hopper" Nash and Nicky have been inseparable friends since childhood. With World War II raging, their last hours as civilians draw to a close, forcing them to make sacrifices that will teach them the true meaning of love.

title: Ratter
description: A beautiful graduate student (Benson) falls prey to an insidious cyber-stalker, watching every moment from the all-seeing eyes of her phone, laptop and television.

title: Reunited
description: Angel Adams is independent, beautiful and successful and has everything a woman wants, except a man. Could that change when her high school crush returns to town? Separated by a twist of fate over10 years ago, they've now been given a second chance.

title: Smash Up
description: A nightclub singer marries a songwriter. His career blossoms and she tumbles downward into alcoholism.

title: Son of Rambow
description: A hilariously fresh take on friendship, family, film heroes and the death-defying adventures of growing up in the video age.

title: Standby
description: In an Irish airport, a woman waiting standby (Mad Men's Jessica Paré) for a flight home to the US runs into an old flame. They discover they're more compatible than ever, but with an ocean between them, is their second chance meant to be?

title: Tarzan's Revenge
description: Featuring two world-class athletes, Tarzan's Revenge stars Olympian Glenn Morris and swimmer Eleanor Holm.

title: That Gang Of Mine
description: A street kid has dreams of becoming a jockey. He gets his chance when he and his gang discover a poor old man who has a championship race horse.

title: The Boo Boo Song & More Nursery Rhymes
description: Sing & dance along to Boo Boo song! Enjoy popular & easy to learn kids songs for babies and toddlers featuring the Boom Buddies, a Nursery Rhyme Kids TV show where your little one can watch & learn baby songs like Baby Shark, Five Little Babies, Old MacDonald Had a Farm, Three Little Kittens, Wheels on the Bus, Wash Your Hands and many more children songs.

title: The Calling
description: A woman is used as a pawn to bring to fruition the rule of the Antichrist.

title: The Creeping Flesh
description: Scientist brothers compete to create living beings. One of them becomes maniacally competitive whenhis brother discovers the skeletal remains of a prehistoric man. Accidentally finding that water activates the growth of blood and tissue on the bony frame leads to the creation of the completed man – a monster who ravages and terrifies the countryside.

title: The Forsyte Saga
description: “The Forsyte Saga" is an epic drama spanning three generations of the powerful Forsyte family at the turn of the 20th century. Beneath the family's imposing veneer lies a festering core of unhappy and brutal relationships.

title: The Great Tours: A Guided Tour of Ancient Egypt
description: The wonders of ancient Egypt have lured tourists for thousands of years; imprinted western art, decorative art, and literature; and enthralled millions since the 1922 discovery of Tutankhamen's tomb. In The Great Tours: A Guided Tour of Ancient Egypt, Egyptologist and curator Melinda Hartwig takes you deep inside the tombs, temples, palaces, and dwellings of the ancient Egyptians.

title: The Last Woman on Earth
description: Ev, along with her husband, Harold, and their lawyer friend Martin, are swimming while on vacation in Puerto Rico. When they resurface, they gradually conclude that a temporary interruption of oxygen has killed everyone.

title: The Old Corral
description: As the sheriff of a small western town, Autry sings his way into a relationship with Eleanor, a singer from a Chicago nightclub who earlier witnessed a murder.

title: The Owls
description: Ten years ago, The Screech was the hottest lesbian band around. But the musicians have fallen into obscurity and unanticipated turmoil. When a pool party goes horribly wrong, a shocking event knocks these friends and lovers even further out of orbit.

title: The Painted Desert
description: Two men find an abandoned baby and fight over the ownership of the child resulting in lifelong rivalry.

title: The Secret Life of the Hospital
description: This film takes viewers to the beating heart of the hospital in a way they've never seen before. It reveals the vast network of people and processes behind the frontline that keep a busy hospital ticking 24 hours a day. Full of surprising facts, The Secret Life of the Hospital focuses on the hundreds of unseen men and women and their roles in the depths of the massive hospital machine

title: The Song to My Heart
description: Having grown up with a musician father, an organic teashop owner wants nothing to do with the music business until a handsome musician enlists her help and rekindles her abandoned dreams. TV-G

title: The Thief of Baghdad
description: A recalcitrant thief vies with a duplicitous Mongol ruler for the hand of a beautiful princess.

title: The Violent Years
description: Paula Parkins is the teenage daughter of wealthy parents whom don't seem to make time for her, so she looks for thrills as the leader of her all girl gang who steal, rob, and rape young men.

title: Thugs Of Hindostan (Tamil)
description: A story about one man’s love for his nation and another’s love for power. An epic adventure filled with edge-of-the-seat thrills and war on the seas.

title: Thuparivaalan
description: Detective Kaniyan Poonkundran who craves for an interesting case to solve, faces a major challenge while solving the mystery of a murdered dog which leads him to capture a powerful rival who proves to be a fitting opponent for him.

title: Whale Rider
description: A contemporary story of love, rejection and triumph as a young Maori girl fights to fulfill a destiny her grandfather refuses to recognize.

title: Wheels on The Bus + More Nursery Rhymes for Babies - Zoobees
description: Enjoy Zoobees popular easy to learn nursery rhymes for babies and toddlers, which the children love to sing and dance along with. Learn these kids songs and new words at the same time. Learn about Twinkle Twinkle Little Star, Five Little Monkeys, Finger Family and more made easy and fun with this preschool playlist.

title: Wheels on The Firetruck & More Kids Songs - Junior Squad
description: Sing & dance along to Wheels on The Firetruck! Enjoy popular & easy to learn kids songs for babies and toddlers featuring the Junior Squad, a Nursery Rhyme Kids TV show where your little one can watch & learn baby songs like Ice Cream Song, Rain Rain Go Away, Five Little Ducks, Colors Song and many more children songs.

title: White God
description: Lili is forced to give up her dog Hagen because its mixed-breed is deemed "unfit" by The State. She and the dog begin a journey back to each other, while all of the "unfit" dogs rise up under a new leader, Hagen.

title: Yukon Gold
description: Season 5 kicks off with a bang for Chris and Nika, but Big Al has a devastating setback and two new camps battle weather and tough mountain roads.

title: A Life at Stake
description: An out-of-work architect meets a married woman who has a business proposition for him. The architect begins to suspect the woman's interest in him is not just financial and may actually be deadly.

title: Alien Intruder
description: Space traveling convicts become the victims of their own fantasies when virtual reality is made to go wrong.

title: Animal Kingdom, The
description: Tom Collier has had a great relationship with Daisy, but when he decides to marry, it is not Daisy whom he asks, it is Cecelia. After the marriage, Tom is bored with the social scene and the obligations of his life.

title: Battle of San Pietro
description: This documentary movie is about the battle of San Pietro, a small village in Italy. Over 1,100 US soldiers were killed while trying to take this location, that blocked the way for the Allied forces from the Germans.

title: British Intelligence
description: Although the home of cabinet minister Arthur Bennett is a hotbed of spies, moles, and double agents, no one knows the true identity of notorious German spymaster Strendler.

title: Cheers For Miss Bishop
description: Dedicated Midwestern teacher Ella Bishop is distressed when her fiance runs off with her vixenish cousin Amy. After Amy dies in childbirth, Ella is left to care for Amy's daughter Hope.

title: Dementia 13 (1963)
description: Following the abrupt death of her husband from a heart attack, scheming Louise Haloran travels to her in-laws estate in Ireland, only to find herself trapped in a creepy, decrepit castle with her ex-husband's demented family.

title: Dick Tracy, Detective
description: A crime thriller based on a comic strip. Dick Tracy is up against a series of murders and all the victims have no ties to one another.

title: Evel Knievel
description: Bio of famed motorcycle daredevil.

title: Fantastic Mr. Fox
description: Mr. and Mrs. Fox live a happy home life with their eccentric son Ash and visiting nephew Kristopherson. That is until Mr. Fox slips into his sneaky, old ways and plots the greatest chicken heist the animal world has ever seen.

title: Ghosts From The Past
description: Hardened ex-con and junkie Viggo comes from a bizarre and mysteriously incestuous family background. Asking himself how he changed from a sensitive boy to a hardened criminal, he begins a painful journey back into his past. Drawing on a rich family archive, Viggo and his sisters struggle to come to terms with the sexual relationships that defined their family.

title: Hollywood Without Make-Up
description: The film consists of archive footage of famous Hollywood stars, mostly home movies showing the stars as themselves instead of playing a role in front of the camera.

title: In Old Colorado
description: Joe Weller has instigated a conflict over water rights between two ranchers. The idea is to have the ranchers do each other in then move in and take over. Hoppy and the good guys won't let this happen.

title: Last Cab to Darwin
description: Rex is a cab driver who has never left the mining town of Broken Hill in his life. When he discovers he doesn't have long to live, he decides to drive through the heart of the country to Darwin, where he's heard he will be able to die on his own terms.

title: Law of the North
description: Hanley shoots a man and then frames Bill Roberts. Being the Judge he then holds court planning to hang Bill but Bill's friends effect his escape. Andy tries to lead Hanley astray by misleading him as to Bill's location.

title: Lemon
description: Isaac has seen better days. His acting career is tanking, his blind girlfriend of 10 years plans to leave him, and his own family singles him out as a constant disappointment. Even as he takes a chance on new romance, he struggles to define his place in a world that has seemingly turned against him.

title: Lie, The
description: Once an idealistic young man with artistic aspirations, Lonnie is stuck and doesn't quite know it. Working at an unfulfilling job, he longs to realize his lifelong dream of becoming a musician.

title: Made In America
description: A celebration of both the unifying power of music and pursuit of the American dream, Made in America is an all-access backstage pass to the one-of-a-kind festival created by rap superstar Jay Z, and directed by Ron Howard. Featuring performances and backstage interviews with many of today's biggest music stars, Made in America shows how one giant celebration of music can change people's lives.

title: Magic Magic
description: In remote Chile, a vacationing young woman begins to mentally unravel; meanwhile, her friends ignore her claim until it's too late.

title: Man of the Frontier
description: Gene and Frog set out to find out who has been causing the accidents at a dam construction site.

title: Not Quite Hollywood
description: The wild, wonderful, untold story of "Ozploitation" films.

title: Nothing Sacred
description: An over-eager newspaper reporter hot on the trail of a story ends up falling in love with his subject. But when her story turns out false, everyone involved goes beyond simple truth-bending to save face!

title: Nymphomaniac: Volume I
description: A self-diagnosed nymphomaniac (Charlotte Gainsbourg), discovered badly beaten in an alley by an older bachelor (Stellan Skarsgård), recounts the erotic story of her adolescence and young adulthood as he tends to her wounds.

title: Nymphomaniac: Volume II
description: NYMPHOMANIAC: VOLUME II continues the story of the self-diagnosed nymphomaniac Joe (Charlotte Gainsbourg) and her adulthood, during which her journey of self-discovery leads to darker complications. With Jamie Bell, Willem Dafoe, Stellan Skarsgård.

title: Rag and Bone
description: The life of a priest seconded to a New Orleans police department begins to fall apart when he is wrongly implicated in the shooting of a suspect. However, it comes to light that the precinct is haunted by the spirit of a deceased policeman, who helps the beleaguered cleric to solve the case and clear his name.

title: Rainbow Ranch
description: An emergency at his Aunt's ranch gets Ed Randall leave from the Navy. He returns to find the water cut off and her note due the next day.

title: Rhythm
description: Karthikeyan, a photo editor in Mumbai, is a widower whose parents wish to see him settled and happy. Chitra, a widow with a son, gives them hope. Little do they realise that their pasts are linked.

title: Ridin' On
description: Bolton has organized a feud between the Rork's and the O'Neil's. He has rustled cattle and killed a man putting the blame on Danny O'Neil. Tom Rork has found a bullet with markings on it that he hopes will clear Danny.

title: Sengottai
description: Thirumoorthy is a corrupt politician who plans to kill the prime minister as he lusts after his position. However, Sekhar, a young police officer, creates hurdles in his path.

title: Swing High, Swing Low
description: In Panama, Maggie King meets soldier Skid Johnson on his last day in the army and reluctantly agrees to a date to celebrate. The two become involved in a nightclub brawl which causes Maggie to miss her ship back to the States.

title: The Big Lift
description: Experiences of two Air Force sergeants during the 1948 Berlin Airlift.

title: The Courageous Dr. Christian
description: A doctor fights an epidemic that breaks out in the poor section of town and tries to get the rest of the town to help out.

title: The Flying Deuces
description: Oliver is heartbroken when he finds that Georgette, the inkeeper's daughter he's fallen in love with, is already married to dashing Foreign Legion officer Francois.

title: The Last Time I Saw Paris
description: Elizabeth Taylor and Van Johnson star as tragic lovers in this film based on F. Scott Fitzgerald's poignant tale "Babylon Revisited.”

title: The Riders of the Whistling Skull
description: A supernatural western! The Three Mesquiteers accompany an archeological expedition to a lost Indian city of gold called Lukachuke.

title: The Second Bed
description: While married to Joyce, Sam begins an affair with a colleague at work and intends to marry her. Unpleasant tide of events brings him back to the mercy of the mother of his children as he hopes to shake off the long arms of the law.

title: They Made Me A Criminal
description: A boxer wins the championship and the same night is accused of the murder of a reporter. He escapes from New York to Arizona but the NY detective is on his trail.

title: Tombstone Canyon
description: Maynard hears the cry of the weird masked "phantom" of Tombstone Canyon. The plot thickens when Maynard discovers a man with a key to his past has been murdered by the phantom.

title: Tough Kid
description: Skipper is serving as trainer and inspiration for his brother Red Murphy training for a world championship title bout. Trouble comes for the Murphys when Red runs up against a gambling syndicate and asked to throw a fight.

title: Vince Giordano: There's a Future in the Past
genre: ['Arts, Entertainment, and Culture', 'Documentary', 'Music Videos and Concerts']
description: For nearly 40 years, Vince Giordano and The Nighthawks have brought the joyful syncopation of the 1920s and '30s to life. A devoted musician and preservationist, Giordano shares his passion for hot jazz with a new generation of music and swing-dance fans.

title: Desert Seas
description: David Attenborough unveils two stunning underwater realms. The flamboyant wildlife of the Red Sea is a stark contrast to the hot muddy Gulf on the other side of Arabia. The Gulf is more famous for sand, oil and war. However, Look a little deeper and it's teeming with life, and according to the latest science it may even come to the rescue of the spectacular but fragile Red Sea reef.

title: Fighting Mustang
description: Sunset has two problems. Rustlers and the disertion of the Kid he helped make a Ranger. The rustlers reside in an area not as yet part of the state and out of the Rangers jurisdiction.

title: Forever Summer: Hamptons
description: Hampton locals Avery, Frankie, Habtamu, Reid, Emelye, Hunter and Juliet have their eyes set on having the best summer of their lives, but tides change when city newcomer Ilan moves out there for the summer. Will Ilan make friends, or waves while trying to fit in? Can lifelong friendships survive the rough seas ahead? Pack your sunscreen, this summer is the hottest one yet!

title: Kasanova
description: Femi, a single dad falls in love with Jessica, a single mother and the music teacher of his son Jason, which causes a conflict of interest between the father and son. The couple fall in love through their children in this battle for love, family and friendship

title: Labor Day
description: Labor Day is "a romance to root for"* starring Kate Winslet and Josh Brolin as two strangers drawn together under incredible circumstances.

title: Modern Love Hyderabad
description: 6 stories of love, growth, resilience and acceptance. Modern Love - Hyderabad is an anthology series that is equal parts a study on modern relationships as it is a love letter to the deliciously diverse city of Hyderabad.

title: Moon Rock For Monday
description: Sydney, 1999. After an unlikely encounter at a train station, a young terminally ill girl named Monday befriends a fugitive teenage boy Tyler. They travel to visit a moon rock that the girl believes might heal her. They road trip across Australia and meet an array of characters along the way.

title: Muddled
description: A romantic movie about Jordan, a successful man who hits a rough patch and begins having marital issues with his beloved wife, Mirabel. His Best friend Earl tries to pull him out of his financial difficulties and help sustain his Marriage, but that path leads him to Dakore, an eccentric Artist who steals his heart.

title: Person to Person
description: A reporter struggles with her first day at work, a rebellious teen attempts to balance her feminist ideals, and a young man reconciles with his ex-girlfriend as her brother threatens revenge. Meanwhile, an avid music lover wanders in search of a rare record, all during a single day in New York City.

title: Shaft
description: Detective John Shaft deals in justice, facing down both criminals and a legal system that thrives on money. But after a racially-motivated murder, Shaft heads out on a personal mission to make sure the son of a real estate tycoon pays for his crimes.

title: Stone Age The Legendary Pet
description: People of Tectonika survived after the fall of technology, only in a form of primitive stone-age era residing along with wild dinosaurs. A passionate dreamer Woody, along with a baby pet dinosaur Moga, sets path to become the best pet trainer but often challenged by mechimaniac villains. Join Woody's journey as the action and comedy will keep your futuristic stone-age era a worthwhile adventure!

title: Taxi Driver
description: After his father dies, a young mechanic moves to the city to drive the old man's taxi. Along the way he encounters assassins and a motley crew of other urban weirdos.

title: The Man Who Cheated Himself
description: A veteran homicide detective who has witnessed his socialite girlfriend kill her husband sees his inexperienced brother assigned to the case.

title: Whitey: United States of America v. James J. Bulger
description: The true story of Whitey Bulger, inspiration for Jack Nicolson's character in Martin Scorsese's THE DEPARTED. Acclaimed documentarian Joe Berlinger lays bare the real story of the South Boston crime boss, including his sensational trial. Key players on every side reveal Bulger's influence on crime and law enforcement.

title: Young Bill Hickok
description: Bill Hickok, assisted by Calamity Jane, is after a foreign agent and his guerrilla band who are trying to take over some western territory just as the Civil War is coming to a close.

title: Ballistica
description: A man has been trained in a deadly form of hand-to-hand combat using ballistics and firearms. He is one of the few Americans who has perfected it, which makes him the CIA's best weapon against International terrorism.

title: Headline Crasher
description: Jimmy Tallant, the care-free son of Senator Tallant, feels compelled to help people he thinks are in distress and, by doing so, stays in trouble of some kind.

title: Jamesy Boy
description: Rage-filled teenager James is never one to back down from a fight. He jumps at the chance to run drugs and guns for a gang and quickly ends up behind bars. He turns his life around in prison thanks to the unexpected friendship he forms with a convicted murderer.

title: Steamboat Bill Jr.
description: The effete son of a cantankerous riverboat captain comes to join his father's crew.

title: The Rest I Make Up
description: When renowned playwright María Irene Fornés stops writing due to dementia, her friendship with a young filmmaker begins a new artistic practice. Made over a decade, The Rest I Make Up is an intimate and collaborative documentary about a visionary artist who lived and wrote outside convention, and a tender story about memory, aging, queer intergenerational friendship, and joyful presence.

title: Black Brigade (Carter's Army)
description: A redneck officer is put in charge of a squad of black troops charged with taking an important bridge from the Nazis.

title: Bolden
description: Bolden imagines the compelling, powerful and tragic journey of Buddy Bolden, the unsung American hero who invented Jazz in the early 1900's in New Orleans.

title: Boot Camp
description: In this white-knuckle thriller, "troubled" teens, including Sophie Bauer (Mila Kunis), are abducted and brought to Camp Serenity rehab where they finds themselves subjected to psychological torture at the hands of camp's deranged administrators.

title: Burning Plain
description: From writer/director Guillermo Arriaga comes THE BURNING PLAIN, a romantic mystery about a woman on the edge who takes an emotional journey back to the defining moment of her life. Oscar-winner Charlize Theron plays Sylvia, a beautiful restaurant manager whose cool, professional demeanor masks the sexually charged storm within. When a stranger from Mexico confronts her with her mysterious past, Sylvia is launched into a journey through space and time that inextricably connects her to these disparate characters, all of whom are grappling with their own romantic destinies. In Mexico, a young motherless girl, Maria (Tessa Ia), lives happily with her father and his best friend until a tragic accident changes it all. In the New Mexico border town of Las Cruces, two teenagers, Mariana (Jennifer Lawrence) and Santiago (JD Pardo), find love in the aftermath of their parents' sudden deaths. In an abandoned trailer, a housewife, Gina (Oscar-winner Kim Basinger), embarks on a passionate affair that will put Sylvia and the others on a collision course with the explosive power of forbidden love.

title: Corregidor
description: The members of a hospital staff in the Philippines try to maintain order while American and Filipino troops defend against a vicious Japanese attack. Starring Otto Kruger, Elissa Landi, and Donald Woods. For trivia buffs: Director Willliam Nigh had 120 movies to his credit...

title: Devil's Cargo
description: When a playboy is found dead, the killer confesses to The Falcon believing he will be found innocent because the victim was romancing his wife. When the killer himself is murdered, The Falcon must unlock several mysteries surrounding the case.

title: Eleven Eleven
description: Tim had a one night stand with a hot alien but didn't tell his wife. When the alien returns to re-ignite their passion, Tim's whole family is at risk.

title: Faith of My Fathers
description: A movie adaptation of John McCain's best selling autobiography, Faith of My Fathers. The film chronicles McCain's experience as a Navy pilot as well as his five years as a prisoner of war in North Vietnam. The film also examines how McCain's military career has shaped the man he is today.

title: Fisherman's Friends
description: A fast living, cynical London music executive heads to a remote Cornish village where he's pranked by his boss into trying to sign a group of shanty singing fishermen. He struggles to gain the respect or enthusiasm of the unlikely boy band and their families. Soon he's forced to reevaluate his own integrity and ultimately question what success really means.

title: Forbidden Jungle
description: A hunter is hired to take an expedition deep into the African jungle to search for a white boy lost in a plane crash years before, and who has been rumored to be living among the wild animals.

title: Ghost World
description: Based on the comic, Ghost World tells the story of neo-cool Enid (Thora Birch) and Rebecca (Scarlett Johansson) who, faced with graduation from high school take a hard look at the world they wryly observe & decide what they really want. When Enid takes an interest in the offbeat Seymour & Rebecca focuses her attention on their mutual romantic fixation Josh, the girls friendship is forever changed.

title: House of 9
description: Nine strangers, with no apparent connection between them are abducted: drugged, kidnapped and sealed in a house together.

title: Moby Dick (1956)
description: Gregory Peck is magnificent as Captain Ahab, the surly sailor who loses his leg to a gigantic, crafty white whale in this stunning visual tribute to the great literary classic. Orson Welles co-stars.

title: Mohawk
description: An artist working in a remote army post is juggling the storekeeper's daughter, his fiancée newly arrived from the east, and the Indian Chief's daughter.

title: Phantom From 10,000 Leagues
description: An unusual radioactive rock on the sea bottom mutates the ocean life into a horrible monster. When charred, radioactive bodies begin to drift ashore a scientist and government agent investigate the phenomenon.

title: Play or Die
description: Lucas and Chloe, two passionate gamers, decide to participate in Paranoia, a very exclusive escape game. Based in a remote, abandoned mental hospital, they find four other participants waiting to play. They soon realize that only one of them will make it out alive.

title: Proud and the Damned
description: A group of five Confederate mercenaries led by Sergeant Will Hansen must choose sides carefully in a small village where they find themselves trapped in the middle of a rebellion.

title: Take This Waltz
description: When a happily married young woman meets the handsome artist across the street, their mutual attraction is undeniable.

title: The End of Time
description: Peter Mettler's film combines elements of documentary, essay, and experimental cinema to create a tour de force that challenges our conception of time - and perhaps the very fabric of our existence.

title: The Flock
description: This film is about a hyper-vigilant employee of the department of public safety who, while training his young female replacement, has to track down a missing girl who he is convinced is connected to a paroled sex offender he is investigating.

title: The Incredible Melting Man
description: An astronaut contracts a disease that causes his flesh to melt. In order to stop the rapid deterioration of his flesh, is to feed on the flesh of other human beings.

title: The Secret of Roan Inish
description: Young Fiona lives with her grandparents in a small fishing village where she takes an active role to unravel the mysterious secrets.

title: True Confessions
description: Two of the finest actors of our time and Godfather co-stars, Robert De Niro and Robert Duvall, star in this must-see tale of two brothers set on a collision course as the result of a brutal murder in 1940s Los Angeles.

title: Athisaya Piravi
description: Kaalayan is killed by goons. In heaven, he opposes and gets sent back in the body of Balu, who has enemies in the form of greedy relatives. Now, he has to fix Balu's life as well as his own.

title: Combat America
description: A documentary recounting the experiences of the 351st Bombardment Group of the U.S. Army Air Forces, based in England during the Second World War .

title: Hanged Man, The
description: A gunfighter who survives his own hanging helps a young widow who is trying to keep a ruthless land baron from taking her ranch.

title: Inside Edge
description: Amidst the greatest show on earth: an India v/s Pakistan cricket series, the politics of Indian cricket is laid bare, its secrets unraveled and truths exposed. The stakes have never been higher, even as they are investigated for corruption, battle lines are drawn for TV rights, endorsement deals and the captaincy of the Indian team. But what is the limit to the price of power?

title: Mind Over Murder
description: A woman's nightmars are coming true. (1979)

title: Shed No Tears
description: A wife convinces her husband to fake his death so they can collect on the life insurance. However, he doesn't know that she has been having an affair for some time, and she has plans for the money - and they don't include him.

title: Shriek in the Night, A
description: Pat Morgan and Ted Kord are rival newspaper reporters always trying to outscoop each other. They join together to solve a series of murders being committed in an apartment building.

title: Southside With You
description: Future president Barack Obama goes on a first date with reluctant attorney Michelle Robinson – which takes the pair to an art exhibit, a screening of Spike Lee’s ‘Do the Right Thing’ and a first kiss outside of an ice cream parlor.

title: West of the Law
description: The Rough Riders arrive to fight Rand, Ludlow and their gang. Buck poses as a preacher, Tim as a preacher, and Sandy as an undertaker. Buck not only wants the outlaws, but also their unknown boss.

title: At Home with the Gils
description: At Home with the Gils follows one of Brazil's most famous musical families during the creation of a historic tour that aims to bring together their different generations on stage. As the Gils gather in a creative retreat in their Rio de Janeiro country house, you will watch the behind-the-scenes preparations for one of the most anticipated concerts of the year.

title: Chinese Connection 2
description: A martial artist (Lieh Lo) seeks vengeance against the fighters who killed his mother.

title: Marry Me
description: A heartbroken pop star (Jennifer Lopez) spontaneously weds a stranger from the audience (Owen Wilson) while live on stage, but their sham marriage turns into a real romance.

title: Runway 34
description: Runway 34 is the story of Captain Vikrant Khanna (Ajay Devgn), a flying prodigy who landed a flight with his eyes closed. Initially hailed by the public as a savior, an investigation led by Narayan Vedant (Amitabh Bachchan) soon enough raises questions that will reveal an entirely different story . Inspired by true events.

title: The Murder of Nicole Brown Simpson
description: Inspired by true events follows OJ Simpson's ex-wife Nicole Brown Simpson in the last days leading up to her tragic death on June 12 1994, as seen from her point of view.

title: 7th & Union
description: Raymundo, a Mexican ex-fighter forms an unlikely bond with a washed up ex-champion whose life and relationship with his daughter are unraveling. The two men join forces to win a bout that could very well save them both and give their families a fighting chance.

title: Angel and the Badman
description: Quirt Evans is wounded outside the home of a Quaker famil. He is taken in and nursed back to health, with particular attention paid to him by their sheltered yet attractive daughter.

title: Awaken
description: In this action thriller, Billie Kope, searching for her sister who disappeared in Mexico, awakens on a remote island with no memory of her abduction. She teams up with a group of survivors, where her skills in Russian Special Forces combat help them resist sinister black operations soldiers who hunt them down and abduct them for reasons unknown.

title: Bebe's Kids
description: When ladies' man Robin meets the beautiful Jamika at a funeral service, he feels he must have died and gone to heaven

title: Boom for Real: The Late Teenage Years of Jean-Michel Basquiat
description: Boom For Real: The Late Teenage Years Of Jean-Michel Basquiat follows Basquiat's life pre-fame and how New York City, the times, the people and the movements surrounding him formed the artist he became.

title: Crooked Arrows
description: A story centered on a Native American lacrosse team making its way through a prep school league tournament.

title: Drums In The Deep South
description: Two old friends find themselves on opposite sides during the Civil War in a desperate battle atop an impregnable mountain.

title: Ftl-dedicalted schema
description: test

title: Phil Tippett: Mad Dreams and Monsters
description: Phil Tippett is a groundbreaking stop-motion animator, designer and filmmaker who has given life to iconic movie creatures throughout his amazing career, from Star Wars to Jurassic Park to Starship Troopers. With exclusive and unlimited access to the collections and archives of Tippett Studio, Mad Dreams and Monsters explores the unique creations and legacy of this Academy Award-winning artist.

title: Predator: The Quietus
description: The unexplainable disappearances of innocently-courting teenagers and a child, plus the brutal slaying of livestock, attracts the international media.

title: Sarkaru Vaari Paata
description: Sarkaru Vaari Paata is a story about Mahi (Mahesh Babu), who believes that financial discipline is a must have quality in everyone. What happens when he encounters Rajendranath who doesn`t respect money. Kalavathi (Keerthy Suresh) is the love interest of Mahi in this action drama.

title: Target for Today
description: A Documentary about one bombing mission over Germany by the American Eighth Air Force, from the initial planning for the mission thru finsl completion of the mission, with all of its intricacies from beginning to end.

title: The Efficiency Expert
description: Errol Wallace is an efficiency expert, who is asked to evaluate a small moccasin factory in Spotswood. On arriving in town, he is confronted by the human faces that are affected by his decisions, reconsiders the rapid modernization he advocates.

title: The Nutty Professor
description: Grossly overweight yet good-hearted professor Sherman Klump takes a special chemical that turns him into the slim but obnoxious Buddy Love.

title: The Painted Desert
description: Two men find an abandoned baby and fight over the ownership of the child resulting in lifelong rivalry.

title: The Parts You Lose
description: Wesley, a young deaf boy, discovers an injured fugitive (Aaron Paul) and secretly helps him recover. Wesley's bond with the man grows that ultimately tests his understanding of right and wrong as the police inch closer and closer.

title: The Secret
description: For the first time in history leading scientists, authors, and philosophers will reveal The Secret, a secret that utterly transformed the lives of those who lived it. Now YOU will know The Secret, and it can change your life forever.

title: The Sundowners
description: Brother is pitted against brother in this tale of fueding ranchers in the old west.

title: Benedict Arnold: Hero Betrayed
description: His name is synonymous with treason but this cinematic documentary shows that Benedict Arnold's heroic contributions to American Independence far outweigh his later change of allegiance.

title: Curse of the Dragonslayer
description: A secret cabal, The Shadow, works to bring about the return of Goth Azul - the Undead God - in the rich world of SAGA, populated by elves, orcs, dwarves and dragons.

title: Dust 2 Glory
description: From acclaimed director Dana Brown (Dust to Glory, Step Into Liquid). This much-anticipated follow-up to Dust to Glory tracks the world's toughest point-to-point desert race, the SCORE Baja 1000.

title: Anacondas: Trail of Blood
description: Even though the two monster snakes from Anaconda: Offspring are dead, a trail of victim's blood confirms that a new generation of snakes has reached adulthood and is preying upon?EVERYTHING. John Rhys-Davies and Crystal Allen return in the fourth installment of the popular franchise.

title: Brave New Jersey
description: On the eve of Orson Welles's legendary 1930 'War of the Worlds' radio broadcast, a small town is fooled into believing that aliens are actually invading America, and face what they now think is their last night alive.

title: Father's Little Dividend
description: In this sequel to The Father of the Bride, newly married Kay Dunstan (Taylor) announces that she and her husband are going to have a baby.

title: Ghost Light
description: An opportunist and liar, Joseph Watkins, puts on a play to impress an actress on the verge of leaving town. However, Joseph soon becomes obsessed with the spirit of the theatre and begins killing those who get in his way.

title: Lady Windermere's Fan
description: A society woman believes her husband is having an affair, a misconception which may have dire personal consequences for all involved.

title: Last of the Clintons
description: Harry Carey (Red River), portrays the rugged Trigger Carson, a noble cowboy who infiltrates an outlaw gang in order to expose their rackets. Ordered to kidnap a young girl, his identity is revealed and he is forced to fight his way out of the gang and bac

title: Meri Pyaari Bindu
description: A successful writer, Abhimanyu Roy (Ayushmann Khurrana) returns to his roots to write an old-fashioned love story, 3 years in the making. This writer's block is called Bindu (Parineeti Chopra). How do you contain this live wire in the pages of a book? When Abhi stumbles across an old audio cassette of their favourite playlist, it sends him down memory lane and his novel starts writing itself.

title: Palooka
description: Knobby discovers young hunk Palooka and trains him to fight the reigning champ, also drunken sot, Al McSwatt.

title: She Shoulda Said 'No'!
description: A chorus girl's career is ruined and her brother is driven to suicide when she starts smoking marijuana.

title: Son of the Renegade
description: In a throw-back to the worse of the 1930's indie westerns, Red River Johnny gathers his friends (most of whom are called some variation of the name Bill) and returns to claim the heritage of his father who was outlawed.

title: Streets of New York
description: Jimmy, an idealistic and hard-working young man, has just arrived in New York City with dreams of making his fortune.

title: The Boys from Brooklyn
description: Two goofy entertainers meet a mad scientist on a jungle island.

title: The Capture
description: A badly injured fugitive explains to a priest how he came to be in his present predicament.

title: The Private Life of Henry VIII
description: Tells how King Henry VIII came to marry five more times after his divorce from his first wife.

title: The Travel Detective
description: CBS News Travel Editor Peter Greenberg shares cutting-edge travel news, must-have information, and insider secrets on navigating the travel process in the public television series The Travel Detective. Each episode has need-to-know tips to improve the travel experience. Featured destinations in this season include Mexico, St. Kitts, Croatia, Hawaii, Alabama and Oklahoma.

title: Wanderers of the West
description: Tom Mallory, posing as a wanted man known as Arizona,is searching the west for the cattle rustler who killed his father, and his only clue is the name Westy Mack.

title: Aadu Magaadra Bujji
description: iddhu, a naughty easy going guy falls in love with Indu. But Indu is the sister of Cherry who keeps on protecting his sister from others' eyes. But on the other hand Cherry he loves Anjali..

title: BOUNDLESS
description: 237 men leave Spain with Ferdinand Magellan as their captain. They search for riches, personal glory and fame. Only 18 of them make it back alive, led by Juan Sebastián Elcano, a noble and charismatic character. Ahead of them are three years of mutinies, treacheries, hunger and death. A story full of adventures and emotions where two confronting characters fight for the same objective.

title: Cruel Train
description: Based on Émile Zola's La Bête Humaine, this stylish film noir is set in Britain during the Blitz. Ruben Roberts discovers he owes everything - job and home - to the sexual favors forced upon his wife by her rich and powerful godfather. Assisted by his wife, Ruben murders him on the Brighton Express. A witness has to be silenced...

title: Fighting Caravans
description: A young frontier scout helps guide a freight wagon train across the country, fighting off Indians and evil traders, while his two crusty companions try and save him from falling in love.

title: Funny Face
description: A fashion editor and a photographer finds a shy bookstore clerk and turns her into the world's most sought after model.

title: Green Eyes
description: A party host is found stabbed in his closet.

title: Gully
description: Three boyhood friends surviving LA's roughest streets find retribution after one night of partying.

title: Love Laughs At Andy Hardy
description: Andy Hardy goes to college after returning from World War II.

title: Panther's Claw
description: When an opera house becomes the scene of a series of grisly murders, the only clue appears to be an animal footprint.

title: Report from the Aleutians
description: A cinematic record of US military operations on the Aleutian Island of Adak to retake Japanese occupied Kiska.

title: Rough Riders' Roundup
description: Now that the Spanish-American war is over, Roy and other Rough Riders become border patrolmen. Their goal is to stop outlaws who are stealing gold from stage coaches and express offices.

title: Shackles
description: Starring D.L. Hughley as a teacher who, desperate for employment, takes the one job he is offered. The job involves teaching inside a prison, a place that is not hospitable to him or to the idea of bettering oneself through education. The teacher stands up to a variety of forces that are against him.

title: The Dance
description: Ivanna and Vicente fall in love one summer, only to realize they've both been keeping secrets.

title: The Sphinx
description: A mute is suspected of murder.

title: An American Ghost Story
description: Paul Anderson (Stephen Twardokus) and his girlfriend Stella (Liesel Kopp) move into a house that is well known for being haunted. Paul, a struggling writer plans to write his first novel about his experiences with the paranormal. What starts out as a fun and exciting adventure, soon takes a very dangerous turn. They quickly realize what you can't see can hurt you.

title: Back Door to Heaven
description: A young kid, who starts out stealing small things in order to fit in with the "crowd", winds up in reform school, and eventually spends much of his life in prison. He later finds that life on the outside can be just as hard.

title: Big Timers
description: A wealthy young society man is dating a beautiful young woman who he believes is also in his "class" because of her beautiful, classically trained singing voice.

title: Brand of the Devil
description: Jolley is the leader of the Devil's Brand gang of rustlers. When Molly Dawson sends for the Texas Rangers, Tex, Jim, and Panhandle arrive pretending not to know each other.

title: Come As You Are
description: Three young men with disabilities (Grant Rosenmeyer, Hayden Szeto, and Ravi Patel) flee their overbearing parents on a road trip to a brothel in Montreal catering to people with special needs. Sam (Gabourey Sidibe), a traveling nurse, drives the three guys across the border as they go on this trip to lose their virginity and embrace their independence.

title: Crazy Love
description: One of the longest-running tabloid stories in New York history is a jaw-dropping saga of obsession, violence, and forgiveness.

title: Dr. Jekyll and Mr. Hyde
description: An early treatment of Robert Louis Stevenson's classic tale, with John Barrymore as the doctor who believes everyone has a dual nature. Featuring Martha Mansfield as the woman loved by Jekyll and Nita Naldi as the dance hall girl seduced by Mr. Hyde.

title: Evocateur: The Morton Downey Jr. Movie
description: Rude, crude and beyond outrageous, Morton Downey Jr. was the profane right-wing prince of the talk show with fistfights, a rabid audience and a mouth that wouldn't quit. Today's extreme tv looks tame by comparison.

title: Fast Bullets
description: Vintage western action starring Tom Tyler (1936).

title: Headin' Home (Silent)
description: The "true story" of baseball great Babe Ruth; Ruth plays himself.

title: High Lonesome
description: When a sudden spurt of murders occurs in the Big Bend country, suspicion immediately falls on a young drifter who just moved to the area.

title: Indestructible Man
description: Scientific experiments accidentally revive an executed criminal and make him impervious to harm, prompting him to seek revenge on his former partners.

title: Madame Behave
description: To help a friend in a lawsuit, Jack Mitchell disguises himself as the "Madame Brown," a missing witness important to the case of the plaintiff. He attracts the romantic attention of two old roues and one hot Broadway showgirl.

title: Melody for Three
description: Dr. Christian takes an interest in a young boy, a violin prodigy, whose mother is a divorced music teacher. His interest isn't just in the boy's music career.

title: Messiah of Evil
description: A young woman goes searching for her missing artist father. Her journey takes her to a strange Californian seaside town governed by a mysterious undead cult.

title: Northwest Trail
description: Mountie Matt O'Brien is assigned to escort Miss Owens to a remote outpost. But when he finds an illegal mining operation there that is smuggling gold across the border, his superior Sgt. Means orders him to leave.

title: Razzia
description: In this searing and mesmerizing drama, five Moroccans from different social and religious strata are pushed to the fringe by their extremist government.

title: Seattle Road
description: Two young artists use love as a safety net against the fear and pain in their lives in order to propel them deeper into their art.

title: Silver Horde
description: A salmon fisherman has to choose between a bad girl and a society doll.

title: Springtime In The Sierras
description: A gang, headed by evil Stephanie Bachelor, is slaughtering game out of season. Roy finds the freezer where the meat is kept, but baddie Roy Barcroft finds him there. A famous fight takes place in the freezer.

title: Stage Door Canteen
description: This delightfully sentimental movie set itself apart from the many other World War II films, made to boost American morale. It documents (via a fictional tale) the real-life story of New York City's Stage Door Canteen.

title: The Basket
description: A picturesque Pacific Northwest community raising its wheat and children in the midst of a nation reeling from World War I sets the stage for The Basket. In a time of pain and prejudice woven against a background of beauty, The Basket ultimately points to triumph and hope in a changing America.

title: The Dead Lands
description: Hongi (James Rolleston), a Maori chieftain's son seeks to avenge his father's murder and the slaughter of his tribe. Outnumbered by a band of villains, Hongi must pass through the Dead Lands and forge an alliance with the mysterious "Warrior".

title: The Leather Burners
description: As rustled cattle have mysteriously disappeared, Bar 20 ranch hand Johnny Travers sends for old friends Hopalong Cassidy and California Carlson.

title: The Sun Sets at Dawn
description: A young man is wrongly convicted and sentenced to be executed. Reporters covering the execution relate the story, each from his own perspective.

title: Yodelin' Kid from Pine Ridge
description: The old west range war story transported to Georgia, with Autry as the hero.

title: Oriental Evil
description: Set in post war Japan, the film tells the tale of a woman looking for her missing brother. Her brother operated a small export business and has suddenly disappeared. Strangely his business partner has also vanished.

title: Race
description: A racing team stumbles onto a plot to destroy the peacekeeping Alliance, leading to a battle of survival with the fate of the universe hanging in the balance.

title: Serena
description: George and Serena Pemberton (Academy Award nominee Bradley Cooper and Academy Award winner Jennifer Lawrence), build a timber empire. They refuse to let anyone stand in the way. Serena discovers George's past and their marriage begins to unravel.

title: Something Beneath
description: A massive cellular organism, highly intelligent and deadly, is living in the sewers beneath a conference center. As attendees of the Clean Planet conference are picked off one by one, a group of scientists band together to stop the ooze in its tracks.

title: Stella Street
description: A feature film based on the British TV comedy featuring the many impressions and creations of actors Phil Cornwell and John Sessions. Between them, they fill Stella Street with some of the most famous people from stage and screen from the last 40 years, plus a few of the local residents, and Jimmy Hill.

title: The Identical
description: The story of twin brothers separated at birth in the Great Depression. With different upbringings, one brother becomes a music legend while the other struggles to find a balance between his passion for music and trying to please his father. Starring Ray Liotta , Ashley Judd, and Seth Green.

title: Vampire Bat
description: A macabre tale of vampire attacks in a small village, from the first golden age of horror! Directed by Frank R. Strayer, written by Hugo nominee Edward T. Lowe, with Lionel Atwill, Fay Wray, Melvyn Douglas, and Dwight Frye.

title: Warning From Space
description: As Japan is rocked by mysterious sightings of UFOs over Tokyo and large one-eyed aliens attempting contact, scientists collaborate to investigate the unexpected rise in extraterrestrial activity. Unbeknownst to them, one of the aliens has already assumed human form and is about to deliver a very important message... that could be humanity's last hope for survival.

title: Wayne Murder Case
description: A police lieutenant and a female reporter investigate a series of murders comitted by a hooded killer in an old dark house.

title: Guru, the Mad Monk
description: Father Guru supplies corpses to medical students, abuses his hunchback servant, and schemes with the vampire Madame Olga in this hand-sewn period piece from the DIY master of mean melodrama, Andy Milligan.

title: Hustling America
description: TV conman Alexis Conran travels across America, he wants to see if his skills in deception and magic will allow him to pull off the hardest cons of all: the so-called Proposition Bets - outlandish sounding wagers that are almost impossible to win unless you know the cunning secret behind them. He's on a personal mission to measure himself against the greatest hustlers in the country.

title: Jack N Jill
description: Young scientist Kesh along with his invention Kuttaps, a humanoid robot sets out to complete his dad’s invention, Jack and Jill. With the help of his friends, he sets up a lab in a forest and finds a subject Parvathy to test on. But, as the test progress, Parvathy starts landing them in deeper troubles and the success of the invention is at risk.

title: Legend of a Warrior
description: Frank Lee doesn't just practice martial arts: for his many students and fans, Frank Lee is martial arts. He is happy to play the role he's cultivated, but there is at least one person who would like to look beneath the superhero mask: his son, Corey.

title: Los Tigres Del Norte: Stories to Tell
description: In their amazing career, Los Tigres del Norte have recorded more than 600 songs, sold 60 million albums, won 7 Grammy Awards and 9 Latin Grammy's. Throughout this voyage through their musical journey, Don Jorge, Hernán, Oscar, Eduardo and Luis share exclusive concert stories, photos, videos, and invite us to enjoy some of the most intimate moments of their life throughout their rise to stardom.

title: My Fake Boyfriend
description: After Andrew is dumped, the plan to make his ex jealous backfires when he meets his real love in this hilarious comedy starring Keiynan Lonsdale, Dylan Sprouse, and Sarah Hyland.

title: Nick Baker's Weird Creatures
description: Nick Baker searches for some of nature's Weird Creatures - from an elusive armadillo that swims through sand dunes, to a lizard that squirts blood from its eyes. For Nick, these are the unsung heroes of evolutionary biology. From scuba diving in Lake Titicaca to a rickety ultralight above the Argentinean desert, Nick's journeys are adventurous

title: Prelude to War
description: The official World War II US Government film statement defining the various enemies of the Allies and why they must be fought.

title: Ray Winstone's Sicily
description: Hollywood actor Ray Winstone takes a trip around Sicily with some old friends, soaking up the island's multicultural history, ancient culture and colourful inhabitants.

title: Super Sheroes
description: A cop, a lawyer, and a hacker form a team dedicated to securing justice for the oppressed and poor citizens... Their passion takes a new turn when an old friend relocates to Nigeria from the UK and becomes a perpetual victim of domestic violence and spousal abuse.

title: The Death Kiss
description: While filming the closing scene of "The Death Kiss", leading man Myles Brent is actually killed. Having played around with, or been married to, most of the women connected with the movie studio, there are lots of suspects.

title: The Last Bus
description: Pensioner Tom travels the length of the UK by bus, retracing the journey he made with his late wife years before, so that he can visit his hometown and his memories one last time.

title: The Pogmentary: Born Ready
description: Paul Pogba is a sports star, a world soccer champion, an iconic Manchester United player with an uncommon personality both on and off the field. But he is coming to a turning point in his life. He dreams of helping his country win a new title, but he is going to have to decide whether or not to stay on with Manchester. A decision that will affect both the future of his career and his family life.

title: THE SECRET: DARE TO DREAM
description: Based on Rhonda Byrne's best-seller, this uplifting story follows a young widow (Katie Holmes) and a mysterious man (Josh Lucas) who helps her and her family transform their lives.

title: The Sessions
description: Athletes know how to expertly take care of their bodies but what about their minds? The Sessions follows mercurial NBA superstar Draymond Green as he works with world renowned self-help guru Deepak Chopra and wellness expert Devi Brown to find a new way to balance his volatile on-court demeanor with the mature adult he has become.

title: 'Allo 'Allo!
description: Wartime sitcom about the French Resistance starring Gorden Kaye and Carmen Silvera, with the farcical events set around a cafe run by René Artois.

title: Attack In The Pacific
description: Overview of the bloody Japan-US conflict

title: Ava & Gabriel: A Love Story
description: Set in Curacao in the 1940s, Ava & Gabriel: A Love Story tells of the painter Gabriel Goedbloed, who arrives from Holland to paint a mural of the Virgin Mary in a local church. Gabriel is black, originally from Surinam. The colonial Antillian society proves less than tolerant towards him, especially after he chooses as his model a young Black teacher, Ava.

title: Beautiful Kate
description: A writer reawakens his childhood trauma from the past when he returns home, at the request of his estranged sister, to grieve their father's impending death.

title: Buffalo Stampede
description: Both Sprague and Jett and their crews are hunting buffalo. Doan is with Sprague and is looking for the Jett outfit where his girlfriend Milly is being held against her will.

title: Finders Keepers
description: Cliff Richard and The Shadows arrive in a small Spanish town for a concert when a U.S. plane accidentally drops a bomb on it. Amid the chaos, The Shadows look for the bomb to return it, a spy plots, search parties collide and The Shadows sing.

title: Her Favorite Patient
description: Macho pilot is treated by a woman doctor. Complications ensue.

title: Kaufman's Game
description: When a stranger offers Stanley, a driven boxer, a specially produced steroid, Stanley finds himself drawn into the ever more violent operations of a powerful organization, where he must enter into a series of tests designed to prove his spirit.

title: Men of the Plains
description: The Government sends Dean, Baxter, and Gordon to investigate a series of train holdups. Travis is behind the robberies and they are soon on his trail.

title: Missing Corpse
description: A feud between rival newspapermen Kruger (Bromberg) and McDonald (Guilfoyle) goes deadly when blackmailing McDonald ends up murdered and his corpse planted in the trunk of Kruger's car.

title: One Body Too Many
description: An insurance investigator arrives at a creepy mansion to protect a millionaire who has had death threats made against him.

title: Operation Atlantis
description: A Secret Service agent is asked by an international organization engaged in research on uranium to investigate acts of sabotage in Africa.

title: Phantom Rancher
description: Cowboy puts on a black mask and a black outfit to fight a gang of land-grabbing crooks.

title: Riddle Ranch
description: Rigging a horse race, Don Carlos wins a lot of money. When he loses his winnings at the gambling table, he shoots the dealer with Horton's gun. Horton is arrested but cannot prove his innocence.

title: Saunkan Saunkne
description: Nirmal and Naseeb are happily married couple. Even after 8 years of marriage they don’t have child. On suggestion of her mother-in-law, Naseeb persuades Nirmal to have a second marriage with her younger sister Kirna. Sharing her husband proves to be a difficult task for Naseeb. And this begins the squabbles between the two wives which lead to comic situation.

title: Stoogemania
description: The hilarious tale of a young man whose entire life is consumed by a passion for the bumbling antics of the Three Stooges! Everywhere he goes he is reminded of scenes from classic Stooges comedies.

title: Stronghold
description: A bank robbery sends two bank gangsters on the run, leading them to a distant farm and an unsuspecting family. Held at gunpoint, the farmer and his wife fear for their lives, but the teenage children welcome the excitement.

title: Tab Hunter Confidential
description: In the 1950s, Tab Hunter is number one at the box office and number one on the music charts. He is Hollywood's most sought-after star and America's boy next door. Natalie Wood, Debbie Reynolds and Sophia Loren are just a few of the actresses he is romantically linked to. Nothing, it seems, can damage Tab Hunter's career. Nothing, that is, except for the fact that Tab Hunter is secretly gay.

title: The Mystery of Sherlock Holmes: Dressed To Kill
description: Sherlock Holmes sets out to discover why a trio of murderous villains, including a dangerously attractive female, are desperate to obtain three unassuming and inexpensive little music boxes.

title: The Racketeer
description: A dapper gangster sponsors an alcoholic violinist in order to win the love of a glamorous divorced socialite.

title: The Twilight Saga: Eclipse - Extended Edition
description: It all begins...with a choice. In the third chapter of Stephenie Meyer's phenomenal Twilight series, Bella Swan is surrounded by danger as Seattle is hit by a string of murders and an evil vampire continues her quest for revenge.

title: Three Came Home
description: In WWII an American author and her husband are arrested and put into a Japanese prisoner of war camp. This is an account of their terrible and harrowing experiences.

title: Tomorrow at Seven
description: People in an old, dark mansion are menaced by a maniac called "The Black Ace."

title: Vigilantes of Boomtown
description: The ranch of Red Ryder and his aunt, The Duchess, is being used as the training site for "Gentleman Jim" Corbett for his upcoming fight in Carson City, Nevada for the heavyweight championship against Bob Fitzsimmons.

title: Welcome To Sweden
description: Welcome to Sweden follows Bruce Evans, who moves from New York City to Stockholm with his Swedish girlfriend Emma, to start a new life.
