description: After the tragic overdose of his estranged friend, Will, a recovering addict, returns home, where he is reunited with Claire, his friend's grieving mother, with whom he begins a secret but volatile affair.

title: Now is Good
description: A teenage girl dying of leukemia compiles a list of things she would like to do before passing away. Topping the list is her desire to lose her virginity.

title: Number One Girl
description: When a former Martial Arts champion is hire to judge a beauty pageant he soon falls for one of the contestants. Trouble ensues with the shadowy figure behind the contest, leading to a Martial Arts showdown before a giant live TV audience.

title: Nuttiest Nutcracker
description: The timeless story of "The Nutcracker" told from the perspective of vegetables.

title: Octopus Pot
description: A broken man finds the one thing he can't live without, only to lose it. He can't bring back the woman he loves, but he can cover the ground with the blood of his enemy.

title: Out of Bounds
description: Daryl's parents ship him off to the big city to live with his brother, hoping he will have a better life there. After a baggage mix-up at the airport, Daryl finds himself in possession of a drug cache, which a drug dealer wants back.

title: Out of Season
description: When a young drifter is forced to stay the winter in a small seaside town, he inadvertently becomes the catalyst for deceit, double crossings and murder amongst the locals.

title: Painter
description: Joanne Marco a wealthy art collector, has been searching for an artistic genius. When she discovers a young, unknown painter named Aldis Brown, she becomes obsessed with him and determined to force his success. She invites him to move into her mansion where she can foster his talent, but their relationship soon deteriorates into psychosexual chaos, fueled by jealousy and delusion.

title: Past Midnight
description: A smart and sexy social worker falls for her client, a man paroled after fifteen years in prison for the murder of his pregnant wife. The social worker begins to uncover inconsistencies in the policerecords that may or may not prove his innocence.

title: Ponzi
description: With open arms, the trusting residents of a Nigerian Close welcome a Politician's long lost American son into their world. He responds to their kindness by establishing a Ponzi Scheme which leaves them in a situation desperate enough to inspire an amateur heist. The heist does not go according to plan.

title: Pororo Bug Songs
description: Pororo and his new bug friends appear! From cute honey bees to cool ladybugs. Come as our lovely bug friends sing the songs you know and love.

title: Pororo Classic Songs
description: Let's go into the classical music world with Pororo! Schubert's 'Military March', Bach's 'Minuet', Necke's 'Csikos Post' etc, Beautiful classic melodies will create the most soothing environment for everyone in the family.

title: Pororo Shark Songs
description: Shall we dance with Pororo, friends and sharks to the cheerful music?

title: Pro in Africa
description: After a ten-year break from football, Emil, 30, a primary school teacher, decides to make a comeback and take the last chance in life to become a pro football player. The best place to experience the great adventure may be in East Africa. Emil wants football to be artistry, but in Kenya his carefree attitude is challenged when he starts to play with KBS, a team from the biggest slum in Africa.

title: Purgatory
description: Purgatory examines the fate of the soul once it leaves the body after death. Drawing from the accounts of approved mystics such as Fulla Horak, St. Faustina Kowalska and St. Padre Pio. Purgatory tells the story of immortal souls living both in human bodies and those that have already left this world.

title: Red 11
description: This gritty sci-fi horror film is based on the research hospital where Robert Rodriguez sold his body to finance his first feature, El Mariachi. Red 11 is the shirt color and number he was assigned.

title: Rory Scovel: Live Without Fear
description: Director Scott Moran documents Rory Scovel behind the scenes and on stage as he attempts six straight nights of fully improvised stand-up comedy at Relapse Theatre in Atlanta, Georgia. Theatre owner Bob Wood has his own story to tell.

title: Scarlet Street
description: Cashier and part-time starving artist Christopher Cross (Edward G. Robinson) is absolutely smitten with the beautiful Kitty March (Joan Bennett). Kitty plays along, but she's really only interested in Johnny (Dan Duryea), a two-bit crook.

title: Slow as Lightning
description: Slow as Lightning tells the story of Jimmie's dreams of winning the heart of his boss' beautiful daughter, Eleanor.

title: Steps
description: Years after a life-altering robbery, a home health aide finds himself assigned to the now-paralyzed gang member who shot him long ago. Face-to-face again, both men must take steps towards recovery, redemption, forgiveness, and love.

title: Still Falling
description: The movie tells the story about love and forgiveness. This story of opposites of feelings - love and hate, faith and doubt, grace and guts, triumphs and regrets.

title: Sue Thomas F.B. Eye
description: Based on a true story, this family-friendly series follows the adventures of a young, hearing impaired woman who has a special gift and goes to work for the FBI in Washington, D.C.

title: Taking Sides
description: After the end of World War II, a famous German conductor is accused of loyalty to the Nazi regime. He argues that art and politics are separate. An investigator thinks otherwise.

title: Tayo's Beep Beep Show
description: It's always fun to be together! Shall we go on an adventure with Tayo and friends?

title: Tayo's NEW Nursery Rhymes
description: Let's learn safety rules and sing interesting colors and numbers with world agitation and brave rescuers!

title: The Bag Girls 2
description: DeAndrea, Nola, Daisy, and Crystal dubbed "The Bag Girls", successful streak of robberies on drug dealers reach its peak. Their plan to exit the operation to resume normal lives is disrupted.

title: The Quest of Alain Ducasse
description: In Theaters Now. An unprecedented look behind the curtain at Alain Ducasse, the multi-Micheline starred chef and one of the world’s most renowned culinary masters and mentors. He tirelessly travels the world smelling, tasting, touching and fearlessly creating ground-breaking new cuisine. French, subtitled in English.

title: The Therapist
description: After losing everything in a divorce to her abusive ex-husband, a penniless and desperate Eloho Odafe decides to help women in similar situations. With the help and support of her friends, Gari and Dumebi, she sets up an agency solely for this purpose. However, everything changes when an offer is made to Eloho that she can't refuse.

title: The Wedding Party 1
description: As their big day arrives, a couple's lavish wedding plans turn into a nightmare that includes exes, fighting parents and uninvited guests.

title: Tinseltown
description: In Hollywood it's all about who you know, and the only person two friends know is a serial killer.

title: Touch
description: Desperately seeking to save his marriage, Brendan goes to the nail salon every day where Tam does more than scrub his hands clean of the oil stains from working as a mechanic. She offers him advice on how win his wife's love again. But soon, they find themselves drawn to each other, an attraction which becomes harder and harder to resist.

title: Twenty Bucks
description: This multi-character comedy follows the path of a single twenty dollar bill in a city neighborhood,focusing on various holders and their intertwining stories, including two convenience store robbers, an estranged father and daughter and a young newlywed couple. Featuring performances by Elisabeth Shue, Christopher Lloyd, Linda Hunt and Spalding Gray.

title: Watermelon Man
description: A bigoted white insurance agent, married with two children, wakes up to find that he is now a blackman! His doctor suggests he might be more comfortable with a black doctor, his neighbors want him to move so their property values won't drop, his wife takes the children and leaves and his boss' desires to capitalize on him as the man to tap the black insurance market.

title: Z Channel: A Magnificent Obsession
description: Z Channel, a once renowned Pay TV station based entirely in Los Angeles, was legendary for its innovative film programming. Operating from 1974 until 1989, it showcased hard-to-find European and Asian cinema, as well as a wide variety of American films,

title: Blood of Redemption
description: Quinn had it all: power, money, a brother who idolized him, and a woman who loved him. But he also had enemies. Betrayed by his inner circle, Quinn is set up and arrested. Upon release from prison, Quinn tries to leave his demons in the past, but "The Company" won't let him leave in peace. Quinn fights, joining forces with his former henchman, The Swede, to take his enemies head on.

title: Cyrano De Bergerac
description: Swordsman-poet helps soldier woo the woman he loves.

title: David Bowie: Out of This World
description: Few artists marked the 20th century like David Bowie did. He was an astonishing and eclectic performer.He was a true artist in every sense of the word. Infinitely changeable and unpredictable, he remains immortal in the people's heart.

title: Defendor
description: Despite lacking any actual superpowers, Arthur Poppington transforms himself into the costumed vigilante Defendor. But danger beckons when our hero tries to protect a young prostitute from an assailant who turns out to be a corrupt undercover cop.

title: Fun With Dick And Jane
description: George Segal and Jane Fonda are the Dick and Jane of this spoof of the upper-middle-class.

title: Gianluca Vacchi - Mucho Más
description: [COMING ON 25-MAY] Gianluca Vacchi is an influencer, businessman and international DJ but the success of one of the most famous Italians in the world, as well as his intimate sphere, still remains a mystery. Mucho Más is an unprecedented journey through the secrets and frailties of a lifestyle pop star, a portrait that goes beyond fame, wealth and irreverence, showing the man behind the celebrity.

title: Night Train
description: While on a night train, three strangers discover a corpse and a box of diamonds. At first, the three scheme to ditch the body and split the fortune - until their greed and paranoia pits them against each other.

title: On Strike For Christmas
description: Joy Robertson goes "on strike for Christmas" because her husband and sons are wrapped up in their own pursuits and providing no help whatsoever with the many Christmas preparations.

title: ReRun
description: On Christmas day, George (Christopher Lloyd), still haunted with regret from the loss of Violet, the 'wayward girl' he loved decades ago, has a second chance to go back in time to relive, reimagine and possibly change his unresolved past.

title: Silks and Saddles
description: College student Jimmy Shaw (Bruce Bennett) inherits a racehorse, named Lightning Lad, and sells stock to fellow students in order to obtain funds for racing the horse. Lightning Lad wins every race he is entered in.

title: Sonic Christmas Blast
description: Santa Claus has made an announcement - he is retiring and has picked the perfect successor - "Robotnikclaus"! Sonic and his sister resolve to persuade Santa to return and set Christmas straight. When the two track down the Santa who made the announcement, they discover he is just a phony robot and the real Santa Claus is being held prisoner.

title: Sonora Stagecoach
description: The Trail Blazers must escort a suspected bank robber to a fair trial, while defending the man from vigilantes.

title: Taking 5
description: Just when BFFs Gabby (Daniella Monet, Nancy Drew) and Devon (Alona Tal, TV's "Veronica Mars") have a chance to get the hottest band to perform a free concert at Highland High, their plan goes up in smoke? literally. Desperate not to be labeled losers for life they resort to plan B: kidnap the band! Now it's limos, laughs and a shot at love with 5 Leo Rise (played by hot pop band, The Click Five..

title: The Stork Club
description: A hat-check girl at the Stork Club saves the life of a drowning man. A rich man, he decides to repay her by anonymously giving her a bank account, a luxury apartment and a charge account at a department store.

title: The Subject
description: A successful documentarian (Jason Biggs) deals with the fallout from his previous film, which caught the murder of a Black teen on tape. As he shoots his latest doc, someone tapes his every move, upending his idyllic life.

title: Unishe April
description: Aditi loses her father when she is eight years old. Her mother Sorojini Gupta, was not at home when he died. Sorojini is a dancer who is away performing at the time of the incident.

title: A Taste of Jupiter
description: Everybody and their brother in Little Italy has a story. But eight people's lives are about to change as Jupiter and Venus come together in the night sky for a once in a lifetime event.

title: All Babes Want To Kill Me
description: A Martial Artist, afflicted with a disease that makes beautiful women want to kill him, goes on a suicide mission to find true love anyway.

title: Arizona Bound
description: The Rough Riders are called upon to help save a stagecoach line.

title: Bad Luck Joe
description: In this hilarious tale of greed, two widows fight over their husband's properties, and bring chaos to any that stand in the way of their inheritance.

title: Broken Star
description: Starlet Markey Marlowe will stop at nothing to ensure everlasting fame and fulfill her desires. But when she's abandoned by her friends and family, Markey ends up alone in a duplex with a reclusive landlord who just may be more dangerous than she is.

title: Cause for Alarm!
description: Mr. Jones is a invalid husband who wrongly thinks his wife and doctor are conspiring to kill him and outlines that suspicion in letter, which causes a serious concern when he ends up dying anyway.

title: Daffodils
description: Leaving her dying father to perform, Maisie explores her parents' heartfelt love story and how it all fell apart through iconic New Zealand hits.

title: Devil's Rock
description: Set in the Channel Islands on the eve of D Day, two Kiwi commandos, sent to destroy German gun emplacements to distract Hitler's forces away from Normandy, discover a Nazi occult plot to unleash demonic forces to win the war.

title: Dosar
description: Kaushik is shattered when he loses his mistress Mita in an accident. The incident also ruins his relationship with his wife Kaberi. Will Kaushik be able to lead a normal life?

title: Eddie Izzard: Wunderbar
description: Wunderbar is a delicious insight into the surreal and fantastical world of Eddie Izzard touching on life, love, history and even her theory of the universe.

title: Election
description: Tracy Flick, a straight "A" go-getter who's determined to be president of Carver High's student body. But when popular teacher Jim McAllister observes the zealous political locomotive, he decides to derail her.

title: George A. Romero's Survival of the Dead
description: On an island off the coast of North America, local residents simultaneously fight a zombie epidemic while hoping for a cure to return their un-dead relatives back to their human state. The master George A. Romero returns with a new entry in the greatest horror series of all time. Combining black humor with his trademark zombie gore and apocalyptic vision, it's a must see for horror fans.

title: Growing Up and Other Lies
description: After struggling for years as an artist in New York City, Jake is calling it quits and returning home to Ohio. On his last day in the city, he persuades his three oldest friends to help him retrace their greatest adventure together: a walk down the entire length of Manhattan.

title: Jesse James At Bay
description: Bank robbery pulled off by the bank officials, not the usual James gang.

title: Judge Priest
description: Judge Priest, a proud Confederate veteran, uses common sense and considerable humanity to dispense justice in a small town in the Post-Bellum Kentucky.

title: Love Lies Bleeding
description: A struggling young couple stumbles upon a cache of dirty money and flees with it, provoking the fury of a corrupt DEA agent and arousing the suspicion of a detective who is determined to find out what's really going on before it's too late.

title: My Pal Trigger
description: Gabby refuses to breed his horse the Golden Sovereign with Roy's. When the Sovereign and Roy's horse escape, Skoville shoots the Sovereign by mistake but Roy is blamed and jailed.

title: No Turning Back
description: An avionics engineer is shortlisted to join one of the first expeditions to Mars. Now, he has to break the news to his wife and children that this will be a one way trip.

title: Northern Frontier
description: A Mountie sets out to infiltrate and break up a gang of counterfeiters.

title: Paula's Best Dishes
description: America's favorite Southern cook Paula Deen rescues recipes and shares stories.

title: Riders of the Deadline
description: When Hoppy's falsely accused young friend is killed while supposedly trying to escape from jail, an embittered Hoppy is blamed and drummed out of the Texas Rangers.

title: Shackles
description: Starring D.L. Hughley as a teacher who, desperate for employment, takes the one job he is offered. The job involves teaching inside a prison, a place that is not hospitable to him or to the idea of bettering oneself through education. The teacher stands up to a variety of forces that are against him.

title: Signs of Life
description: A wounded German paratrooper named Stroszek is sent to the quiet island of Kos with his wife Nora, a Greek nurse, and two other soldiers recovering from minor wounds. Billeted in a decaying fortress, they guard a munitions depot.

title: Six-Pack Annie
description: Busty, blonde and beautiful, Six-Pack Annie seeks to help her Aunt Tess raise $5,000 for the family diner...by trying to find a rich daddy.

title: The Eyes of Laura Mars
description: A Manhattan photographer (Dunaway) develops the frightening ability to see gruesome murders before they take place. She teams up with a veteran police lieutenant (Jones) in order to unravel the mystery of her condition and put the perpetrator behind bars.

title: The Hospital
description: From director Arthur Hiller comes this caustic comedy starring George C. Scott as a besieged doctor in a bureaucratic mega-hospital who meets a free-spirit just in time.

title: The Hurricane
description: A Polynesian sailor – unjustly imprisoned after defending himself against a colonial bully – is relentlessly persecuted by his island's martinet French governor.

title: The Monster Walks
description: People in an old dark house on a stormy night are menaced by a killer ape.

title: The Sharkfighters
description: Victor Mature leads a group of Navy scientists to test a shark repellent designed to save the lives of fliers forced down into the sea. How to test the repellent? Mr. Mature offers himself as shark bait...

title: They Call It Murder (1971)
description: Trials of a small-town attorney. Fine cast.

title: Allied
description: Allied is the story of intelligence officer Max Vatan, who in 1942 North Africa encounters French Resistance fighter Marianne Beausejour on a deadly mission behind enemy lines.

title: Alone Yet Not Alone
description: ALONE YET NOT ALONE is based on the inspirational, true story of Barbara and Regina Leininger, two immigrant sisters forced to embark on a journey of faith that will lead them through the darkness of war into the light of freedom.

title: Americaneast
description: "AmericanEast" bravely explores the experience of Middle Eastern immigrants living in post-9/11 L.A.. When the U.S. government declares a severe risk of terrorist attacks, passions run high and drama unfolds for an eclectic mix of Arab-Americans.

title: Bullseye!
description: While a corrupt nuclear scientist (Michael Caine) and his partner-in-crime (Roger Moore) plan to sell a cold fusion formula to a foreign entity, they're being impersonated by crafty con artists (also Caine and Moore) who want a piece of the action!

title: Dude Perfect Best Of Trick Shots
description: Recognized as one of the most influential and most watched content creators in the world, Dude Perfect is a group of 5 best friends who have given a whole new meaning to the term sports entertainment. Now they are sharing never-before-told stories behind 10 of their favorite trick shots.

title: Little Tough Guy
description: The son of a man sentenced to death for a murder he didn't commit vows to become a criminal himself. He starts his own street gang, and their crime spree is financed by a mysterious young man.

title: Radio Days
description: In this star-studded portrait of the 1940s, Woody Allen weaves together a young boy's comical memories with zany stories from the golden age of radio to create a delightful tapestry of hilarious vignettes...and a beautiful eulogy to a bygone era.

title: A Lawman is Born
description: An outlaw falsely accused of murder realizes the only way to clear himself is to become a lawman.

title: Adventures of Super Mario Bros 3
description: Another set of adventures starring the now-classic kids' heroes, The Super Marios Bros. This time Koopa has escaped from a Banishment Zone to battle the Super Mario Bros. And he has a powerful new weapon, the Koopa Kids - Koopa's bratty, yet lovable, offspring! It's the irrepressible Marios versus wild kids gone amuck in outrageous comedy adventures.

title: Allies
description: August 1944. A team of British soldiers led by a US Captain are dropped behind enemy lines in France on a mission that could shorten the war. As nothing goes according to plan, commando Sergeant Harry McBain and Captain Gabriel Jackson know they must put aside personal animosity if the mission is to succeed. Inspired by true events, Allies tells the story of friendship and survival.

title: Amazon Queen
description: An idyllic riverboat cruise through the exotic Amazon rainforest becomes a nightmare for the crew and passengers when thieves take over the boat in search of a downed plane carrying their stolen money. As the female captain and her passengers band together to overtake their captors, the jungle will make its own judgement on who survives.

title: April Apocalypse
description: After years of yearning for the girl next door, Artie finally builds the courage to woo her... only to find out the girl of his dreams and best friend, April, is moving away - sending Artie into a deep depression. Three years later, the lion inside tells Artie to "go find April and make her yours". Artie crashes his car on the way... and wakes up a week later in the middle of a zombie outbreak.

title: At the Gate of the Ghost
description: In this worthy adaptation of the Japanese film "Rashomon," a young monk is left to determine the truth behind three competing perspectives after a bandit's disturbing murder trial.

title: Bodysnatch
description: Returning to his hometown to reconnect with his best friend and the girl that got away, Steve, a recent college graduate, finds himself faced with a problem that's literally out of this world: an invasive race of alien body snatchers.

title: Caged Animal
description: A former kingpin of the streets, Miles "Cain" Skinner, is doing life in prison. He is feared and respected among the inmates. When Cain's nemesis, Redfoot, is transferred to the same prison, Cain's wrath is unleashed in a savage showdown with no surrendering, no retreating, no mercy.

title: Captain Kidd
description: The unhistorical adventures of pirate Captain Kidd revolve around treasure and treachery.

title: Eye in the Sky
description: An operation to capture terrorists in Kenya is complicated when a young girl enters the kill zone, triggering an international dispute over the implications of modern warfare.

title: Fist of the Red Dragon
description: Action-packed with Donnie Yen kicking his adversaries in the role of "Beggar Su". A young Beggar Su getting addicted to opium and manipulated by a scheming imperial prince to fight against WFH and assassinate a righteous general. As expected, Beggar Su repents and gangs up with WFH against the prince in a climactic battle. Guess who you have helping the prince, the White Lotus sect of course...

title: Happy House
description: Their relationship on the rocks, a couple heads to a bed & breakfast to work things out. But from the moment they arrive at The Happy House it's one disaster after another, and they soon begin to suspect they've wandered into a real life horror movie.

title: Ithaca
description: With his older brother off to war, fourteen-year-old telegram messenger Homer Macauley comes of age in the summer of 1942.

title: Kept Husbands
description: Blue collar steelworker Richard Brunton (McCrea) saves two of his fellow workers after an accident at a factory. In gratitude, his boss, millionaire Arthur Parker invites Richard for dinner with his family.

title: Larva
description: Now in New York City, watch Red and Yellow's incredible abilities while they explore the city. A whole new adventure on a bigger scale!

title: London
description: London is a drug laden adventure that centers on a party in a New York loft where a young man (Chris Evans) is trying to win back his ex-girlfriend (Jessica Biel).

title: Mad To The Max: Hoon Nation
description: With a blend of 'reality Mad Max' and the seamy underbelly of suburbia, Hoon Capital is a definitive study of Hoons and takes you on a journey into a subculture vilified by the popular media. Even if you're not interested in cars and car culture, this documentary is a must see, as we watch bogans, hoons and blokes strap in for the short ride to impoundment.

title: My Very Ghanaian Wedding
description: Two strangers, from different cultures and different views, meet by chance again, and a beautiful, meaningful relationship begins. An unplanned pregnancy and a mother insistent on tradition. Can their love overcome these obstacles?

title: Nathan's Kingdom
description: A young autistic man struggles with his teenage opiate-addicted sister, and together they risk their lives to find a fictitious kingdom with the potential of changing their lives forever.

title: One Step From Me
description: Tatiana leads a routine life and her boyfriend just left her. Motivated by her friend, she sets out on a trip to the beaches of Costa Rica in search of love, passion, and new relationships to experiment with.

title: One Way Pendulum
description: A suburban clerk living in a dream world eventually sets an imaginary murder trial in motion.

title: Outbreak 2020
description: A greedy business man partners with some young scientists to make a virus with the aim of infecting people to fall sick, thereby also make an antidote to sell to the sick in other to make huge profit. Things go ugly in the process of releasing the virus and now the whole world is in a mess.

title: RBG
description: A candid look at Ruth Bader Ginsburg’s exceptional life and career as a long-standing U.S. Supreme Court Justice, champion of women’s rights, and pop culture icon.

title: Rock On 2
description: Adi decides to host a grand charity concert along with the rest of the members of Magik, a rock band. However, the constant opposition from the local authorities makes things very difficult for them.

title: The Big Wheel
description: A brash young midget car race driver lives in the shadow of his famous father, a drunken womanizer, who was killed in an accident years earlier.

title: The Mystery Man
description: In need of funds, a newspaper reporter (Robert Armstrong) pawns a police revolver that was given to him after he cleared up a criminal case. When the gun is used in a murder, he's suspected of the killing.

title: The Summer I Turned Pretty
description: A new series based on the New York Times bestselling book. Every summer, Belly and her family head to the Fishers’ beach house in Cousins. Every summer is the same ... until Belly turns sixteen. Relationships will be tested, painful truths will be revealed, and Belly will be forever changed. It’s a summer of first love, first heartbreak and growing up – it's the summer she turns pretty.

title: Thunder Alley (1985)
description: Richie, a farm boy, achieves his dream of becoming a rock star as the lead vocalist and guitarist for an up-and-coming rock group. However, Richie and the band are constantly tempted by this exciting lifestyle of easy sex and dangerous drugs.

title: What Did You Do In The War Daddy?
description: Comedy master Blake Edwards weaves his wacky madness in this first-rate WWII story of a by-the-book Captain who is ordered to take over a troop of misfit soldiers led by Lieutenant James Coburn.

title: White Sky
description: When three campers witness an alien mothership descending on their town and turning the population into "Altered" human beings, they team up with a reclusive stranger who offers to guide them to safety. As they're chased deep into the forest and one of them becomes infected, they realize there's nowhere to hide from the Altered horde that seems intent upon finding and assimilating them.

title: A Novel Romance
description: Novelist Nate Shepard becomes roommates with his ex-girlfriend's pal Jenny, whose boyfriend recently died of an overdose. Despite the circumstances, the two inexplicably connect.

title: Beer
description: A Madison Avenue ad-agency executive devises a highly successful commercial campaign to sell beer.

title: Candyman (2021)
description: The housing projects of Cabrini Green neighborhood have been terrorized by a killer. Now, Anthony McCoy and his girlfriend have moved into a luxury loft in a now gentrified area. An encounter with a resident exposes Anthony to the story behind Candyman.

title: Chinni (UHD)
description: A generational curse, comes true in a senseless act of injustice to Ponni and her family. Driven to seek vengeance by Sangaiya, with whom she shares a bitter past.

title: Confessions of An Action Star
description: This mocumentary follows the rise and fall of Chip and Dales dancer Frank Sledge who becomes a martial arts action star. A passionate homage to the 80s-90s action movies full of Cameo's directed by the renowned stuntman Brad Martin and starring director/stuntman David Leitch as the lead.

title: Coyote
description: While working for his eccentric uncle, a thirty year old social misfit befriends an illegal Mexican laborer. Together they hatch an ill-advised plan to rescue the immigrant's mother and sister who are being held captive across the border.

title: Dawn of the Dragonslayer
description: After Will's father is killed by a dragon, he embarks on an epic journey to seek vengeance against the vicious monster. While undergoing intense training on how to slay the beast, he uncovers a mysterious family connection and prepares to avenge his father's death before his secret is discovered.

title: Defining Moments
description: A series of transformational, comedic stories intertwine. A couple must decide their next steps; an estranged family reconnects; and a daughter deals with the advancing Alzheimer’s disease of her father played by Burt Reynolds in his final performance.

title: Finally Found Someone
description: This Filipino romantic comedy film tells the story of April's (Sarah Geronimo) heartbreak that goes viral when her reaction to being ditched on her wedding day is posted online. She meets Raffy (John Lloyd Cruz) a PR expert, hired by the father of the groom and tasked to help her move on.

title: Man, Pride and Vengeance
description: When stalwart Spanish soldier Don José meets the beautiful Carmen, he becomes instantly obsessed with the mysterious gypsy woman. After she cheats on him with his Lieutenant, José kills the officer during a brawl, flees the city and becomes a bandit.

title: Salesmen
description: Four door-to-door salesmen struggle to get by while pursuing an analog profession in a digital world. They unwittingly begin selling propaganda for a cult, whose popularity sweeps the city, leaving the salesmen as the only people who can stop it.

title: Tango Shalom
description: When a Tango dancer asks a Rabbi to enter a dance competition, there's one big problem-due to his Orthodox beliefs, he's not allowed to touch her! But the prize money would save his school from bankruptcy, so they develop a plan to enter the competition without sacrificing his faith, and the bonds of family and community are tested one dazzling dance step at a time.

title: The Addams Family 2
description: Everyone's favorite spooky family is back! Distraught that their children are growing up, Morticia and Gomez decide to cram Wednesday, Pugsley and Uncle Fester into their haunted camper for one last family vacation. What could possibly go wrong?

title: The Captain
description: When the windshield of his commercial airplane shatters at 30,000 feet in the air, a pilot and his flight crew work to ensure the safety of the passengers and land the plane

title: Tin Star
description: The third and final season of Tin Star is the most thrilling, and darkly comic rollercoaster ride yet. It tells the story of Jack, Angela and Anna returning to Liverpool, where their story began twenty years ago, to face their deadliest enemies in a battle with the past to win freedom in the present. But instead, our heroes are forced to face up to the devastating truth about who they really are.

title: Trocadero
description: A newspaper columnist and host of his own national network radio program, interviewing more film personalities on his show than any other commentator, is searching for a story for a Sunday column.

title: Untangled
description: When an absence of communication reveals a love triangle, much more than lies come to light.

title: Wolfgang Climbing Team
description: Follow the incredible adventures of the Wolfgang Climbing Team as they head off to far-flung destinations. From a 45 days rock climbing expedition in the Canadian Arctic to a climbing - sailing expedition in Greenland or the Venezuelan Jungle. This is serious business! These Belgian climbing heroes are on an infinite quest for unclimbed big walls and share their passion for rock, music and pain.

title: 100 Days to Live
description: When a serial killer abducts a young woman's fiancé, she must race against the clock to discover the identity of the killer and, more importantly, his motive.

title: American Refugee
description: In the midst of societal collapse, the Taylor family's last chance at survival is a neighbor's bunker, where their fate lies in the hands of the family patriarch. Supplies are scarce, and when tensions rise, no one knows who can really be trusted.

title: Beneath Hill 60
description: The extraordinary true story of Oliver Woodward. It's 1916 and Woodward must tear himself from his new young love to go to the mud and carnage of the Western Front. Deep beneath the German lines. Woodward and his secret platoon of Australian tunnelers fight to defend a leaking, labyrinthine tunnel system packed with enough high explosives to change the course of the War.

title: Football Fans: Under Their Skin
description: Robbie Lyle is lifelong Arsenal fan. As founder of AFTV, Robbie is a YouTube star with millions of followers worldwide. But as a black supporter Robbie has sadly experienced racism in the game. In this heartfelt documentary, Robbie reveals how he has been racially abused, not only in the past but also today, and he meets other fans who speak out about their experiences of racism in football.

title: Forsaken (2014)
description: After abandoning his gun and reputation as a quick-draw killer, John Henry returns to his hometown in hopes of repairing his relationship with his estranged father.

title: Life's Rewards
description: Jared, seemingly all-knowing, has the answer for everyone around him. But can he take his own advice? As he embarks on his dream of opening a business, he comes to realize how complicated his life is becoming. Between finances, love, well-meaning friends and family, Jared is tested in ways not even the Navy could prepare him for. Will he allow others to help, or will his pride get the best of him?

description: The story of Maria Paradis, a gifted piano player, who lost her eyesight as a child. Desperate to cure their daughter, her parents entrust Maria to Dr. Franz Mesmer. Using his technique, Maria recovers her sight. But this miracle comes at a price.

description: The Chinese government sends a band of elite narcotics officers to uncover the truth behind the ambush of two Chinese commercial vessels traveling down the Mekong River. The road to justice is, however, paved with dangerous and deadly obstacles.

title: Some Girl(s)

title: Staten Island
description: The lives of three residents of New York's Staten Island intersect as they struggle to get ahead.

title: The Bronx Bull
description: A combination "before the rage" and "after the rage" of world middleweight boxing champion Jake LaMotta's tumultuous life and times.

title: The Derby Stallion
description: An alcoholic former horse-trainer perceives in a fifteen-year-old boy a unique gift of horsemanship and makes it possible for the boy to conceive his dream and pursue it.

title: The Mule
description: A first time drug mule is caught by law enforcement.

title: Thomas & Friends: Blue Mountain Mystery The Movie
description: When trouble strikes at the Blue Mountain Quarry, Thomas is sent to help his Narrow Gauge engine friends. While there he discovers a mysterious small green engine hiding in the tunnels. Why is the little engine hiding? Thomas is determined to get to the bottom of the mystery but discovering the truth is harder than he imagined!

title: White Rabbit
description: A dramatic comedy following a Korean American performance artist who struggles to be authentically heard and seen through her multiple identities in modern Los Angeles.

title: Enemy of the Law
description: To get the money hidden by Gray before he was caught, the Rangers send Perkins to prison to become his friend. When the two get out, Perkins is unaware that Gray has printed the map to the loot on the bottom of his foot.

description: When James Conrad, Director of Entomology at the LA Museum of Natural History, travels to a remote area of the northern wilderness to go salmon fishing, he is thrust head first into a life and death battle with the deadliest insects he has ever encoutered

description: After several locals are viciously murdered, a Louisiana sheriff starts to suspect he may be dealing with a werewolf.

description: A violent Thai gang is abducting and killing women around Thailand. Samin and his friends, having had loved ones abducted, have joined together to break up the gang of kidnappers.

description: A military agent must bring down a terrorist's sinister plot. When Hamza, an elite solider, uncovers a sinister plot involving illegal arms dealing, he finds himself in a web of murder and corruption.

Olie's route takes him over gruelling snowy mountain passes high up in the Himalayas, battling intense heat in the northern plains, and being drenched to the bone by monsoon rains as he walks through the rural heartland of the country.

title: Arctic Dogs
description: An Arctic fox works in the mailroom of a package delivery service, but wants to be doing the deliveries.

title: Chambal
description: Subhash is a young and dynamic IAS officer, His relentless and uncompromising way of working sends shivers across the corridors of power, cutting across political and business circles. Being incorruptible and principled, his idealism and righteousness soon become a threat to the entire system.

description: Eugenio convinces his reluctant family to take a vacation together for the first time ever. Despite their busy schedules, they drop what they’re doing to join him for a month in Morocco where they embark on a crazy, emotional and hilarious adventure.

description: In this one-hour special of "Dr. G: Medical Examiner," Dr. Jan Garavaglia reveals the secret truths she's uncovered over the years. If there's one thing she's learned from performing 6,000 autopsies, it's that many of those people did not need to die. Now she'll reveal the five leading reasons that Americans end up in the morgue.

title: Invasion of the Body Snatchers
description: One by one, the residents of San Francisco are becoming drone-like shadows their former selves.

description: This documentary was produced in 1944 by the United States Coast Guard, featuring on-the-spot coverage of the initial assault on fortress Europe.

title: Panchayat
description: With the rise of an opponent against Pradhan Ji, village politics of Phulera heats up. Unable to stay neutral, Abhishek sticks his neck out for Pradhan's family.

title: Penny Serenade
description: A young couple falls in love while on a trip to Japan, but face tragedy when an earthquake causes June (Irene Dunne) to lose the baby she is carrying.

title: Pokémon the Series: Black and White - Full Season
description: Ash and his friends Iris and Cilan have foiled Team Rocket's latest evil plan, and a new danger lurks on the horizon! But first, Ash is ready to take on the region's ultimate challenge: the Unova League, where he'll face familiar rivals and new opponents! Meanwhile, Iris is having trouble connecting with her stubborn Dragonite

title: Queen of Blood
description: When an alien ship crash-lands on Mars, a rescue ship sent to look for survivors. They find just one: an alien vampire, who starts killing the crew by sucking their blood.

title: The Friendliest Town

description: Capturing the generational spectrum with a right pinch of raw humor, he is all set to do VANSH KA NAASH... Wait what? But Papa toh kehte hai bada naam karega? Our very own homegrown boy, Sumit Sourav is all ready to take the dig on parenting, purpose of life, and much more. Watch him as he hits the stage with his unflinching comedy and truth bombs.

title: Sumit Sourav: Vansh Ka Naash (UHD)
description: Capturing the generational spectrum with a right pinch of raw humor, he is all set to do VANSH KA NAASH... Wait what? But Papa toh kehte hai bada naam karega? Our very own homegrown boy, Sumit Sourav is all ready to take the dig on parenting, purpose of life, and much more. Watch him as he hits the stage with his unflinching comedy and truth bombs.

title: The Angel Levine
description: A Jewish tailor's shop has gone up in flames, his daughter has married outside the faith and his wife is slowly dying. When he decides to give up on God, a mysterious man appears as a guardian angel and must overcome his skepticism.

title: The Disappointments Room
description: Dana, her husband David and their 5-year-old son Lucas start a new life after moving from the hustle and bustle of Brooklyn, N.Y., to a stately old manor in the quiet countryside. After settling in, Dana starts to experience terrifying visions and dreams that she cannot explain. The mystery grows when she stumbles upon a secret room in the attic.

title: The Dunning Man
description: Broke and newly single, Connor Ryan returns to Atlantic City to rebuild his life with the last source of income he's got: a few condos in a low-rise complex in the shadow of the city's newest casino. Even worse? His tenants refuse to pay him.

title: The Great Flamarion
description: Flamarion, expert marksman, is entertaining people in a show which features Connie, a beautiful woman and her husband Al. Flamarion and Connie fall in love and decide to get rid of the alcoholic husband.

title: Black Road
description: In the autonomous, lawless rebel State of Jefferson in 2029, an ex-military drifter risks his life to protect a mysterious woman from her dangerous ex, aided only by his A.I. implant Clyde, who proves partner and friend.

title: Born to Fight
description: A boxer on the run from gamblers.

title: By Love Possessed
description: Lana Turner and Jason Robards star in a drama of passion and propriety as blue-blooded pillars of a small New England town who must face their defiant son's (George Hamilton) increasingly rebellious behavior.

title: Faults
description: The parents of a young girl hire an expert to help her escape the clutches of an evil and dangerous cult but soon find out their mystical powers maybe greater than anyone imagined.

title: Modern Love Mumbai
description: Modern Love Mumbai explores 6 unique yet universal stories of human connection and love in its varied forms – romantic, platonic, parental, sexual, familial, marital, self love. Inspired by the beloved New York Times column, this edition of the hugely popular original version of the same name, explores love in all of its complicated and beautiful forms against the city of dreams, Mumbai.

title: Veera
description: Muthu returns to his village and learns that the girl he wanted to marry is dead. In the city, he ends up marrying his boss's daughter. But, the previous girl returns and he's forced to marry her too.

title: A League Of Their Own
description: Tom Hanks and Geena Davis star in this big-league comedy based on the real-life exploits of the All-American Girls Baseball League.

title: Blue's Clues
description: Blue's Clues is a breakthrough play-along show which allows its preschool audience to step inside and become part of a bright, fanciful computer animated world.

title: Bound
description: The lesbian romance between a newly-released ex-con, and the girlfriend of a Mafia money-launderer, has a mercenary dynamic. The girls plan to walk off with a suitcase of $2 million cash, but the Mafioso finds out a little too soon.

title: Break Every Chain
description: A police officer's battle with alcoholism, depression, and devastating loss; and the true story of how God changed his life forever.

title: Courage Under Fire
description: A military investigator with his own troubled combat history interviews multiple soliders to discover if a female pilot - killed in the line of duty - deserves the Medal of Honor. With Matt Damon, Lou Diamond Phillips.

title: Earth to Echo
description: When a trio of boys begin receiving a strange series of signals on their phones, they discover a small alien who has become stranded and needs help to find his way home. This journey, full of wonder and adventure, is their story, and their secret.

title: Gaza Mon Amour
description: Gaza, today. Sixty-year-old fisherman Issa is secretly in love with Siham, a woman who works at the market with her daughter Leila. When he discovers an ancient phallic statue of Apollo in his fishing nets, Issa hides it, not knowing what to do with this mysterious and potent treasure. Yet deep inside, he feels that this discovery will change his life forever.

title: Independence Day
description: HD. When alien invaders lay waste to planet Earth, it's up to a select group of survivors to make a last-ditch stand in this sci-fi smash.

title: Marathon Man
description: A graduate history student is unwittingly caught in the middle of an international conspiracy involving stolen diamonds, an exiled Nazi war criminal, and a rogue government agent. .

title: Office Space
description: Tired of his mind-numbing job, Peter adopts a negligent attitude as a way to get fired. But instead, he's propelled into the ranks of upper management.

title: The Angriest Man in Brooklyn
description: HD. A curmudgeon who is told by his doctor that he has only 90 minutes to live and sets out to make amends with his family and friends.

title: The Guardian
description: Action-packed drama that takes you inside the never-before-seen world of the elite Coast Guard Rescue Swimmers. Reeling with grief from a mission gone tragically wrong, a legendary swimmer is given a mission he doesn't want – training raw recruits.

title: The Miseducation of Bindu
description: When a bullied teenage girl forges her mother’s signature to test out of high school, hijinks ensue as she struggles to pay the test fee before the end of the day.

title: The Namesake
description: HD. An Indian immigrant family learns to revere tradition while accepting American ideas in this film based on the novel.

title: The Ugly Truth
description: A romantically challenged morning show producer (Katherine Heigl) is reluctantly embroiled in a series of outrageous tests by her chauvinistic correspondent (Gerard Butler) to prove his theories on relationships and help her find love. His clever ploys, however, lead to an unexpected result. Directed by Robert Luketic.

title: The Winslow Boy
description: When a young boy claims he was expelled for something he didn't do, his father sacrifices everything to defend his family's honor. Based on Terence Rattigan's celebrated play, adapted and directed byDavid Mamet.

title: Valley Girl
description: Julie, a girl from the valley, meets Randy, a punk from the city. They are from different worlds and find love. Somehow they need to stay together in spite of her trendy, shallow friends.

title: Adventures of Sonic the Hedgehog
description: Sonic the Hedgehog, the most fearless hero on Planet Mobius, uses his supersonic speed and teenage irreverence to thwart the comedically despicable Dr. Robotnik. Sonic's idolizing little buddy, Tails, tags along on every fast-action, gag-driven adventure.

title: Ancient Love Poetry
description: Ancient Love Poetry follows Shang Gu, once a leader of the four immortals, who falls into a deep sleep after sacrificing herself in a trial that lasted 60,000 years. Shang Gu wakes up many years later, and memories of what happened 300 years ago were completely wiped. But her former lover, Bai Jue, never forgot about her.

title: Castle in the Ground
description: After the death of his mother (Neve Campbell), Henry (Alex Wolff), a rudderless teenager, befriends his charismatic but troubled next-door neighbor (Imogen Poots), becoming embroiled in a world of opioid addiction and violence.

title: Delicious
description: France, 1789, just before the Revolution. With the help of a surprising young woman, a chef who has been sacked by his master finds the strength to free himself from his position as a servant and opens the first restaurant.

title: Lawless Land
description: Jeff arrives in town to see the Sheriff only to find him just killed. The culprit is Clay Wheeler. When Jeff becomes friendly with Letty, Clay sends his man Ortega to kill him.

title: Lost Transmissions
description: When an acclaimed music producer goes off his medication for schizophrenia, his friends chase him though the LA music scene to help commit him to a psychiatric hospital, revealing the troubling inadequacies of our mental health care system.

title: Once Upon A Time
description: Based on the best-selling fantasy novel, Once Upon A Time is a story of epic battles, deep passion, and the powerful forces that drive mortals and gods alike toward revenge, loyalty, and eternal love.

title: Pinkfong Wonderstar
description: Pinkfong comes from the planet Staria and crash lands in Wonderville. In Wonderville, Pinkfong finds a perfect friend and problem-solving partner, Hogi. With Pinkfong's magical powers and Hogi's great ideas, they work together to help their friends in Wonderville - and beyond.

title: Return of the Tiger
description: Shrewd'n'suave Chang Wong and his redoubtable female partner devise an elaborate plan to take out a heroin drug ring led by the nefarious Paul. Moreover, Wong also works for a rival dope-dealing organization in order to further stir things up.

title: Rimba Racer
description: The story continues as Tag and his friends return to compete in the 14th season of the RIMBA Grand Prix - the world's most prestigious racing competition! After the previous season's chaotic events, Tag is determined more than ever to claim the grand prize and become RIMBA Grand Prix champion in what he hopes will be a clean and fair race.

title: Spirit
description: When Kelly and her father move to New Orleans after the death of her mother, strange things start happening in their new home. Kelly is convinced that the house is haunted by a ghost who needs her help. Her father does not believe her, so she enlists her friend Cole to help discover the truth.

title: Sweetness In The Belly
description: A moving story of Lilly (Dakota Fanning), a child abandoned in Africa as a child. Lily is forced to flee Ethiopia for England when civil war breaks. She befriends Amina (Wunmi Mosaku), an Ethiopian refugee who has fled the same war. Together they begin a mission to reunite people with their scattered families.

title: The Black Tent
description: Set in the African desert, a British soldier romances the native chief's daughter and helps the tribe fight off Nazi attack.

title: The Creatress
description: A bestselling author seeks literary revenge against a critic who authors her fake memoir much to the delight of her agent.

title: The Positive Alternative
description: Climate change has fundamentally impacted and changed the lives of farmers in Australia. Watch the story of different farmers dealing with changing climate conditions and how they create a positive alternative. Each of them shares their personal experiences and provides solutions to create a sustainable food industry. The Positive Alternative provides both dramatic yet inspiring stories about...

title: Tulsa
description: It's Tulsa, Oklahoma at the start of the oil boom and Cherokee Lansing's rancher father is killed in a fight with the Tanner Oil Company, but Cherokee plans revenge by bringing in her own wells.

title: Winterhawk
description: Set along the northern boarder in 1840. After his son dies and half of the Blackfoot nation is wiped out, an indian chief approaches the white man for smallpox serum. Instead of help, he is attacked.

title: And Your Name Is Jonah
description: A couple whose son had been diagnosed as mentally retarded, and was institutionalized, are shocked to discover that the diagnosis was wrong, and that their son is deaf, not retarded.

title: Brick Lane
description: A young Bangladeshi woman, Nazneen, arrives in 1980s London, leaving behind her beloved sister and home, for an arranged marriage and a new life. Trapped within the four walls of her flat in East London, and in a loveless marriage with the middle aged Chanu, Nazneen struggles to accept her new life. Then one day, the hotheaded young Karim comes knocking at her door.

title: Brother Jekwu
description: The local village champion who leaves his familiar village in Nigeria and is transported to Kenya to work for a no-nonsense female boss.

title: Charge and Bail
description: A dramedy about a highflying young lawyer from the upper-class who finds herself posted to a "charge and bail" law firm during her youth service year. A culture clash between the haves and the have-nots about what it means to find yourself in a place that you least expect.

title: Diary of a Sergeant
description: Harold Russell, an American soldier who lost his hands in a training accident, tells the story of his medical rehabilitation at Walter Reed Army Medical Center in Washington DC.

title: Dixiana
description: In antebellum New Orleans, two men vie for the affections of a beautiful young girl during Mardi Gras.

title: I Love America
description: Jump into the adventures of Lisa, a single woman who decides to take another chance on love by catapulting her life from Paris to Los Angeles. Reuniting with her best friend Luka, together they embark on a mission to give Lisa a fresh start. From awkward dates to a touching surprise encounter, Lisa comes to understand that the journey to love is a journey towards forgiveness and herself.

title: Jail Bait
description: Vic Brady draws young Don Gregor into a life of crime. He then blackmails Gregor's plastic surgeon father into fixing up his face so he can evade the cops.

title: LA OCTAVA CLAUSULA
description: At first glance, Cat and Borja are the perfect couple but like every marriage, they hide secrets, lies, and infidelities from each other. All of them will surface the same night they receive an unexpected visitor.

title: LOL: Last One Laughing
description: What is the best tool to make a comedian laugh? Another comedian! That is why comedians won't be playing on their own in this fourth season. Instead, they will be joined by their best comedian friends to compete in DUOS, each willing to do whatever it takes to make the other DUOS laugh and ultimately earn LOL's trophy, arguably the most coveted comedy award EVER.

title: LOL: Qui rit, sort!
description: Philippe Lacheau and Alexandra Lamy welcome Camille Lellouche, Ahmed Sylla, Éric Judor, Ramzy Bedia, Alice David, Melha Bedia, Panayotis Pascot, Just Riadh, Audrey Fleurot and Gérard Darmon to be part of a unique experience. They'll have to remain unflappable while trying to make their opponents laugh. Whoever laughs will be eliminated. The winner will receive €50,000 towards a charity.

title: Of Human Bondage
description: A young man finds himself attracted to a cold and unfeeling waitress who may ultimately destroy them both.

title: Planet of the Vampires
description: After landing on the mysterious planet Aura, the spaceship's astronauts become possessed by formless alien vampires which are trying to reach Earth.

title: Silence
description: Two Christian missionaries who face the ultimate test of faith, travel to Japan in search of their missing mentor during a time when Christianity was outlawed and their presence forbidden.

title: Story of David - The Hunted, A
description: History making period in David's life when his popularity with the people incurred the wrath and jealousy of King Saul who then sent him into exile.

title: The Devil Bat (1940)
description: A deranged scientist (Bela Lugosi) develops an aftershave lotion that incites his giant bats to kill in this Producers Releasing Corporation (PRC) hit. A fiendish performance by Lugosi, directed by Jean Yargrough (House of Horrors, She-Wolf of London).

title: The Golden Child
description: A detective who has a knack for finding lost children is recruited by a Tibetan High Priestess to find the Golden Child, a Bhuddist mystic youngster who has been kidnapped by an evil sorcerer.

title: The Hunter
description: A bounty hunter who makes his living finding bail-jumpers is stalked by a fugitive vowing revenge. Based on the real life adventures of Ralph Thornson.

title: The Rainbow Bridge Motel
description: After reserving their dream wedding package at Niagara Falls, Dean and Darren learn they've booked themselves in a run-down motor lodge sandwiched between two chemical plants.

title: Tim Allen: Men Are Pigs
description: In this special from 1990, Tim Allen proves men are pigs as he discusses family and the differences between women and men. In "Men are Pigs" , you see the groundwork for his successful show, "Home Improvement".

title: Undone
description: Tumble Leaf is a series aimed at preschoolers, set in a whimsical land where a small blue fox named Fig plays each day and discovers adventure, friendship and love around every bend in the path. Children will be enriched by narratives that promote play, the fun of learning and understanding the world around them.

title: Young Sherlock Holmes
description: This film portrays what might have happened if Sherlock Holmes and Dr. John H. Watson had met as teens at school in England.

title: 10 Days In Sun City
description: A young couple head to Sun City in the hopes of getting out of the hood and to a life of luxury by entering in a Queen of Nigeria pageant.

title: 180 South
description: Jeff Johnson retraces the epic 1968 journey of his heroes Yvon Choulnard and Doug Tompkins to Patagonia.

The Women's War was a 1929 revolt in British Nigeria, where a group of women took a stand against social and economic injustice. This historical drama follows the story of these women and their crusade.

title: 93 Days
description: 93 Days is a 2016 Nigerian drama thriller film directed and co-produced by Steve Gukas.[2] The film recounts the 2014 Ebola outbreak in Nigeria and its successful containment by health workers from a Lagos hospital.

title: A Trip To Jamaica
description: A newly engaged couple's romantic vacation in Jamaica turns into a mischievous adventure that tests their union in wild and unexpected ways. Ayo Makun, Funke Akindele.

title: Accidental Spy
description: After he is blind sided by his cheating girlfriend, an IT specialist becomes entangled in a reality show mix up with Nigeria's most infamous cartel without realising it.

title: Alakada Reloaded
description: Following a young girl from a poor family, who as a result of her inferiority complex, engages in the act of making up stories about her financial and social status in order to fit in with the crowd.

title: Banana Island Ghost
description: When a man dies in a car accident, he bargains with God to receive three more days back on Earth to find his soul mate.

title: Children of Mud
description: Kicked out of their home after being abused and then accused of being witches by their superstitious aunt and her lecherous husband, a young girl and her blind brother go looking for a televangelist they saw on TV in search of healing, hope and love

title: Couple of Days
description: Three couples, each in different phases of romance, head to Ibadan for a fun and frisky holiday. But secrets soon start to spill, causing trouble in paradise.

title: Crazy People
description: Ramsey Nouah returns to Nollywood in search of an impostor who seems to be getting away with making public appearances at movie sets and other celebrity hangouts whilst feigning to be the real Ramsey.

title: Delivery Boy
description: A teenage suicide bomber on the run and his newfound ally, a young prostitute, must rely on each other to survive the night while searching for answers to the terrible secrets that made them who they are.

title: Disguise
description: A young man and woman disguise themselves as the opposite sex to find the answer to an age old question, in the hopes of winning a huge cash-prize.

title: Dolly & Friends: The Making of a Soundtrack
description: Dolly & Friends: Making a Soundtrack features Parton in the recording studio with famed producer Linda Perry for an exclusive look inside the making of Dumplin' with artists Alison Krauss, Elle King, Macy Gray, Miranda Lambert, Mavis Staples, and Rhonda Vincent.

title: Fix Us
description: Fix Us tells a story of three young ladies who take on a journey of faith and fate. When Nadie, Chioma and Jaya run into each other at an audition, they are bound by their common dream to be movie stars and form a friendship that can hardly be broken.

title: Gold Statue
description: Two young men, Wale and Chike are in search of a 'Gold Statue' believed to have been a diety inherited by their generation. In trying to locate where the supposed statue is located, they go through a series of unimaginable ordeals.

title: Hire a Woman
description: A young man attends a college reunion with a fake girlfriend in an attempt to make his ex jealous.

title: My London Slave
description: Ada, a Nigerian based medical doctor, moves to the UK, and marries her best friend’s brother, Raymond, a British- Nigerian. Her “overseas” fairytale quickly turns into a dreadful nightmare as Raymond starts to reveal a sinister side and Ada discovers the real reason he married her.

title: My Wife and I
description: An illiterate man and his family head to a church summit, but their car breaks down. They have no choice but to stay with an unfriendly but wealthy family member.

title: The Bird Catcher
description: Norway 1942 - Fleeing the Nazi round-up of Jews, 15-yr-old Esther is trapped and alone on a Nazi-occupied farm.To what lengths must she go to survive?

title: The Ghost and The Tout
description: A young woman encounters a ghost after an unfortunate incident. Soon her life is thrown into series of dramas that only her can see and understand.

title: The Women
description: Four female middle aged friend who bare many secrets about each other congregate in a resort one weekend, on the occasion of one of their birthdays and unintentionally unravel their secretes.

title: Up North
description: Love, friendship and family politics collide when a young rebellious heir from a wealthy family is sent away to national service in northern Nigeria.

title: When Love Happens
description: A wedding planner sees the clock ticking on her own chance to get married. Constantly striking out, she starts online dating and finally finds gets lucky in love.

title: When Men Promise
description: A man believes the only way to keep his wife under check is by getting her pregnant yearly to keep men away from her. In her grit to fight back, she has to avoid getting pregnant.

title: Abe & Phil's Last Poker Game
description: Striking up an unlikely friendship with a womanizing gambler, Dr. Abe Mandelbaum's stay in a new retirement home becomes interesting. When they each try to convince a mysterious nurse they are her long-lost father, Abe's new friendship is tested.

title: Across the Plains
description: Two brothers separated when young meet as adults, one good and one bad.

title: Arrival
description: When mysterious spacecraft touch down across the globe, an elite team - led by expert translator Louise Banks (Academy Award nominee Amy Adams) - races against time to decipher their intent.

title: Awful Nice
description: Estranged brothers Jim and Dave must travel to Branson together when their father dies and leaves them the lake home.

title: Bang Bang Baby
description: 1986. Alice is a 16-year-old girl living in a small town in the North of Italy. Her life suddenly changes when she finds out her long-deceased father is still alive. Alice begins a descent into Milan's criminal underbelly, diving into the dangerous world of the ‘ndrangheta out of love for her father. By the time she tries to get out of that world, it might already be too late.

title: Becky Sharp
description: Based on the novel Vanity Fair by William Makepeace Thackeray.

title: Bloody Sunday
description: The infamous story of Bloody Sunday unfolds from the perspective of Ivan, the activist who led the peaceful protest march in Northern Ireland on January 30, 1972, that took a violent turn when British soldiers opened fire on a defenseless crowd.

title: Breaking the Maya Code
description: Based on archaeologist Michael Coe's book and filmed in nine countries, Breaking the Maya Code is the amazing story of the 200-year struggle to unlock the secret hieroglyphs of the ancient Maya.

title: Breakneck
description: Two extreme sports athletes enter a contest in the hopes of winning the cash prize. They soon learn that the "game" is a dangerous cross between an evil reality show and a frightening ritual.

title: Enakkoru Magan Pirappan
description: Balu's mother desperately wants a grandson, but his wife gives birth to a baby girl. As Balu's mother suffers a heart attack, he ends up showing his friend's newborn son as his own to make her happy.

title: Fatal Crossing
description: A high flying tech entrepreneur wakes up in a bloody car with no memory and is suspected of killing the boyfriend of a woman he has falling in love with during his blackout.

title: Foxfire Light
description: Joanna, a recent college graduate, decides to leave her manipulating mother and stay within the Ozarks in order to find herself. What she finds is a small town filled with romance and the promise of love.

title: Full Moon High
description: A high-school football star's life changes after his strange, right- wing father takes him on a vacation to Transylvania...where he is bitten by a werewolf.

title: House on Haunted Hill
description: A millionaire offers $10,000 to 5 people if they agree to stay overnight in a large, spooky house. When you consider that the millionaire is Vincent Price, and the film is directed by Schlock master William Castle, they are in for a long, bumpy night.

title: In Search of Greatness
description: IN SEARCH OF GREATNESS is a groundbreaking documentary that reveals the true nature and nurture of the greatest athletes of all time

title: Interlude in Prague
description: Wolfgang Amadeus Mozart's unconventional presence in Prague begins a series of dramatic and tragic events that become a tangled, violent web. Overwhelmed by the intrigue that surrounds him, Mozart creates the astonishing opera Don Giovanni.

title: Joe's War
description: Family pride and fearless determination inspire Joe Caruso to join the Marines to do his duty in today's War on Terror. But when Joe comes home, his attempts to return to normal are challenged by his PTSD from two tours of duty.

title: June Again
description: A twist of fate gives June a reprieve from a debilitating illness. She sets about to put her family and business back on track. When it goes awry, she sets out on a journey and discovers she needs help from the people she was trying to help.

title: Killers From Space
description: A scientist believes aliens plan to attack Earth!

title: LOL: Last One Laughing Spain
description: In this second season, the villain Santiago Segura and his henchman Xavier Deltell sell the crazy Marina LOL resort to Silvia Abril and Carolina Iglesias. For its inauguration they invite 9 new comedians and a repeater. Whoever manages to last 6 hours without laughing will win 100,000 Euros to donate to a charitable cause.

title: Maren Morris: Live From New York
description: Maren Morris celebrates the launch of her new album, Humble Quest, with a one-night-only intimate performance live from the historic Sony Hall in New York City. Humble Quest (available March 25) documents Maren's journey to redefine humility on her own terms. This performance offers fans the chance to hear her new songs live as Maren kicks off her Humble Quest tour.

title: Meet Bill
description: A guy fed up with his job and married to a cheating wife reluctantly mentors a rebellious teen.

title: Paperman (1971)
description: A prank that starts with a group of college students creating a fictitious person so they can get a credit card develops into a plot that leaves three of them dead.

title: Paranormal Activity 4 - Rated
description: It has been five years since the disappearance of Katie and Hunter, and a suburban family witness strange events in their neighborhood when a woman and a mysterious child move in.

title: Queen Of Hearts
description: An Italian couple defy both their families and marry for love. Four children later, they are running a diner in England. Humorous, dramatic, sad – everything a movie should be.

title: Robot And Frank
description: ROBOT & FRANK is a hilarious and heartwarming story about finding friends and family in the most unexpected places.

title: Rock My World
description: A rock band bursts onto the scene and then their frontman disappears on the eve of a European tour.

title: Steam Room Stories: The Movie!
description: Failing cosmetics magnate Sally Fay (Traci Lords) will stop at nothing to possess the waters of the Steam Room to help lift her sagging empire. What she doesn't count on is the Steam Room Guys banding together to thwart her evil plans.

title: Steven Banks: Home Entertainment Center
description: In this brilliant one-man show from 1989, the mild-mannered, thirty-something Steven Banks arrives home after a long day at his dead-end corporate job, still dreaming of being a rock star, but plagued by procrastination.

title: Sticky Fingers
description: Two aspiring musicians become the custodians of a trunk containing 900,000 dollars in drug money. They proceed to "borrow" from the case until the underworld bosses arrive and want their money back.

title: The Browsing Effect
description: The seemingly endless possibilities of dating apps sends a group of friends into a whirlwind of sex, jealously, and self-doubt in this ensemble comedy that examines dating culture in the age of swiping.

title: The Middle Distance
description: In the wake of his estranged father's death, successful Los Angeles executive Neil Mercer (Ross Partridge, Stranger Things) travels to the Midwest for the first time in years to help sell the family home.

title: The Nightmare Gallery
description: An anthropology professor's obsession with a paranormal mystery threatens her job, marriage, and sanity as she fights to find a missing student.

title: The President's Mystery
description: A millionaire starts a new life. (1936)

title: The Ring Thing
description: When a woman proposes to her girlfriend by accident, she finds that they each have very different expectations of their future.

title: The Visitors
description: Bill, Martha and their little child Hal are spending a quiet winter Sunday in their house when they get an unexpected visit from Mike Nickerson and Tony Rodriguez.

title: This is Not Berlin
description: 1986. Mexico City. Seventeen-year-old Carlos doesn't fit in anywhere: not in his family nor with the friends he has chosen in school. But everything changes when he is invited to a mythical nightclub where he discovers the underground nightlife scene: post punk, sexual liberty, and drugs that challenges the relationship with his best friend Gera and lets him find his passion for art.

title: Tunisian Victory
description: Documentary made by the U.S. Army Signal Corps.

title: Golden Voices
description: Raya and Victor built a shared career as the Soviet Union's most beloved film dubbers. As the USSR collapses, the Jewish couple must immigrate to Israel and reinvent themselves to find employment. A charming comedy about disrupting dynamics, starting anew, and rediscovering yourself in the most unexpected places. Golden Voices is also a stirring tribute to the redemptive power of cinema.

title: 48 Hours to Live
description: Fresh out of rehab and wanted by both sides of the law, Wyatt is seriously thinking about building a different kind of life for himself. But when his sister is murdered, he finds himself entangled in a game of revenge on the LA club circuit.

title: After We Leave
description: A gritty sci-fi crime drama about a man who has a once in a lifetime chance to emigrate off Earth, if only he can find his estranged wife and convince her to come with him.

title: Dr. Brinks and Dr. Brinks
description: After husband and wife aid workers die in a plane crash, their grown children are reunited for the first time in years.

title: Flight
description: An airline pilot saves a flight from crashing, but an investigation into the malfunctions reveals something troubling.

title: Friends Don't Let Friends
description: A violent breakup leaves one man dead and a group of friends dispatched into the desert to dispose of the evidence.

title: Fritz the Cat
description: Fritz is a college-age cat who dabbles in drugs, radical politics, and hedonism. Film traces Fritz's sexual and political exploits from an East Village pot party to an orthodox synagogue to a Harlem bar brawl and riot to an odyssey across America.

title: Hit the Saddle (1937)
description: Greedy rancher McGowan wants to have a local wild horse sanctuary closed, so he can capture and sell them while Tucson tries to break up Stony's marriage to a sexy, gold-digging saloon girl.

title: Jaws of the Jungle
description: Ceylonese natives are forced to flee into the dangerous jungle after an attack by swarms of vicious vampire bats.

title: Karamoja
description: The filmed record of an expedition to the African interior, with scenes of animal life and native customs and practices.

title: Mark of the Hawk
description: Tension in British occupied Africa (1957)

title: Oh my God!
description: Jesus comes back to earth to speak his verb and proclaim the imminent arrival of the Kingdom of Heaven. But this time, he chooses to make a video of his earthly passage.

title: Snow White
description: The ageless tale of a beautiful young princess whose jealous step- mother orders her killed so that she will be "the fairest in the land." When the henchman takes pity on her, he takes her to the house of the seven dwarves.

title: Soldiers of the Damned
description: 1944, Romania. A group of German soldiers is tasked with taking a scientist into a forest that is believed to be haunted.

Grieving his late wife, Ove has largely given up on life until a boisterous young family moves in next door and forces him out of his shell in this heartwarming tale that reminds us that life is sweeter when it's shared. Includes English subtitles-user may need to turn subtitles on.

title: Angel On My Shoulder
description: The Devil arranges for a deceased gangster to return to Earth as a well-respected judge to make up for his previous life.

title: Apartment 143
description: A team of parapsychologists sets out to investigate a series of anomalous phenomena taking place in a newly occupied apartment.

title: As Far as the Eye Can See
description: A former piano prodigy lives a withdrawn life on his farm in northern Texas. Scheduled to make a comeback to performing in his first public appearance in years, he threatens the show after injuring his hand.

title: Bells of San Angelo
description: Gridley is mining silver from an old Mexican mine and bringing it into the USA thru a passage into his worthless mine. Border guard Rogers suspects Gridley and finally finds the secret entrance to the Mexican mine.

title: Devil's Party
description: Adults who grew up as slum kids meet later in life, but murder disrupts their reunion.

title: Donkey Punch
description: After meeting at a nightclub in a Mediterranean resort, seven young adults continue partying aboard a luxury yacht. But when one of them dies in a freak accident, the others argue about what to do, which leads to a ruthless fight for survival.

title: Fugitive Of The Plains
description: Billy joins an outlaw band led by woman to clear his name of their crimes, which are being blamed on him.

title: Gemma Bovery
description: Life imitates art when Gemma Bovery and her husband Charles move to a charming old farmhouse in the very same Norman village where Flaubert's classic novel Madame Bovary was written a century earlier. A cheeky literary mash-up, a sensuous romance, a witty feminist commentary and a heady celebration of French provincial life. Includes English subtitles-user may need to turn subtitles on.

title: I'm Not Here
description: Haunted by the tragic memories of his past, every sound Steve hears reminds him of specific event in his life. While connecting the events of his past to make sense of his present, he begins to realize that time isn't the enemy he thinks it is.

title: Ida
description: After encountering a long lost relative, a young novitiate nun in 1960s Poland discovers a shocking family secret dating back to the terrible years of the Nazi occupation, and embarks on a revelatory journey to uncover the mystery of her own past. Winner of the 2015 Academy Award for Best Foreign Film.

title: Lore
description: After being abandoned by their Nazi parents at the end of World War II, five German siblings embark on a harrowing journey across their war-torn country. Led by the eldest, 14 year-old Lore, the children are forced to confront their parents' actions and the reality of the new world in which they find themselves.

title: Meru
