description: Three elite climbers struggle to find their way through obsession and loss as they attempt to climb Mount Meru, one of the most coveted prizes in the high stakes game of Himalayan big wall climbing. Meru is the story of that journey, an expedition through nature's harshest elements and one's complicated inner demons, and ultimately on to impossible new heights.

title: Raging Bull
description: The life of boxer Jake LaMotta (Robert De Niro), as the violence and temper that leads him to the top in the ring destroys his life outside of it. Directed by Martin Scorsese.

title: Satanic
description: College students visit old Satanic Panic-era sites in Los Angeles. They end up finding themselves saving a girl from a human sacrifice. Only this “victim” turns out to be much more dangerous than the cult from which she escaped.

title: The Curse of Sleeping Beauty
description: Thomas unexpectedly inherits a property with a mysterious curse.

title: The Great Gabbo
description: One of Hollywood's earliest musicals, The Great Gabbo stars von Stroheim as an egotistical ventriloquist who casts a Svengali-like spell upon an ingenue against a backdrop of singularly strange numbers.

title: The Magic Sword
description: The son of a sorceress, armed with weapons, armour and six magically summoned knights, embarks on a quest to save a princess from a vengeful wizard.

title: The Man Who Walked Around the World
description: A young Scottish boy starts blending whisky in a grocer's shop in 1820, little did he know the result would go on to become one of the world's most recognised brands. From Emmy and triple Bafta-winning director Anthony Wonke, The Man Who Walked Around the World is an exploration of what it takes to become an icon in popular culture.

title: The Warlords
description: In the midst of the Taiping Rebellion of the 1860s, three men take an oath to and "blood brothers," pledging loyalty to one another until death, but soon become embroiled in a web of political deceit.

title: The Way You Look Tonight
description: Ditched after a perfect date, Peter turns to an online dating site guaranteed to find his perfect match, but notices strange similarities between all his matches and that first amazing date.

title: Vanquisher
description: Operating under the code name “Gunja,” a female Special Ops agent with the Royal Thai Police is recruited to join Claire, an American CIA agent sent to track an Al-Qaeda member.

title: Way Down East
description: A naive country girl is tricked into a sham marriage by a wealthy womanizer, then must rebuild her life despite the taint of having borne a child out of wedlock.

title: West of Her
description: Two alienated young strangers participate in a mysterious guerilla street project, traveling the country in search of connection and answers to life's most haunting questions.

title: Who Gets The Dog
description: Six years after saying "I do," Olive (Silverstone) and Clay (Kwanten) call it quits. And although they split amicably, both want custody of their beloved dog Wesley. With everything at stake, can man's best friend find a way to reunite the couple?

title: Bachchhan Paandey
description: Akshay plays a gangster and Kriti a journalist. The twist in the tale occurs when the two characters meet and discover their common passion for cinema, which brings along action, drama and humor, because while the gangster is a wannabe actor, the journalist aspires to be a director.

title: Boyfriend School, The
description: Painfully boring Gus isn't exactly ladies' man material – at least not until his meddling romance writer sister makes him the buff and bronzed main character in the romantic fantasies of his dream girl, Emily.

title: Re:MARS Luminaries
description: Explore machine learning, automation, robotics, and space through the lens of luminaries-distinguished professors, leading CEOs, and head scientists.

title: Scared To Death
description: From a slab in the morgue, a dead young woman tells the bizarre tale of how she got there, through a maze of murder involving a hypnotist, a midget and a mysterious figure in a blue mask.

title: The Ghost and the Whale
description: In the town of Bodega Bay, Joseph went to sea with the love of his life and returned alone. The mystery deepens upon Joseph's exoneration in her disappearance, while a reporter stirs the pot of suspicion and the wrath of a vengeful family.

title: The Kids in the Hall: Death Comes to Town
description: When the mayor of Shuckton, Ontario is murdered after the town's bid for the 2028 Summer Olympics was rejected, a small-time criminal is the main suspect. However, an obese man named Ricky suspects the real murderer is still at large and enlists his friend Marnie to help investigate the crime. Meanwhile, Death waits in a motel room to collect the souls of dead Shuckton citizens.

title: Veyil
description: A journey to Sidharth's (Shane Nigam) teenage memories. He reminiscences his school life and love story with Sruthi which he ends for the sake of his brother. His childhood is lost being envious of the extra care his brother received due to critical heath issues. Later, Sidharth helps his mother financially but lands up in a problem. Trouble follows him and he faces the consequence of his doings.
A sexy, dramatic thriller about interconnected romantic life in the 21st century, featuring a terrific ensemble cast led by Anthony Hopkins, Jude Law, Rachel Weisz and Ben Foster.

title: Alien Invasion: S.U.M1
description: After a hostile race of aliens take over the planet, humanity retreats underground to live out their lives in giant bunkers. S.U.M.1, a committed young military rookie who has lived his whole life underground, is sent on a mission to the surface.

title: Alpha Gateway
description: Grieving over the loss of her husband in a car crash, a particle physicist decides to travel to a parallel universe to find him again. Unfortunately, this has dire consequences for the rest of her family.

title: And Then We Danced
description: A passionate coming-of age tale set amidst the conservative confines of modern Georgian society, And Then We Danced follows Merab, a competitive dancer who is thrown off balance by the arrival of Irakli, a fellow male dancer with a rebellious streak sparking an intense rivalry and a forbidden desire. Includes English subtitles-user may need to turn subtitles on.

title: Black Widow
description: Danny's new fiancée, Olivia, is beautiful, brilliant, and charming. But Danny's friend Melanie isn't so taken. She knows the secrets that have left Olivia a very rich serial widow. Now, it's Melanie turn to turn the tables on the cunning bride-to-be.

title: Boss Engira Bhaskaran
description: Bhaskaran, a college dropout, along with his friend Nallathambi starts a coaching class for students in order to win the love of a young professor, Chandrika.

title: Croc
description: A beach town in Thailand loses good chunks of its tourist trade when a killer croc is cut loose and left to roam. The feeding frenzy also raises the stakes between two competing croc farmers who are liable to lose an arm and a leg if business drops off.

title: Dhoom
description: An edge of the seat action thriller revolves around a suave motorbike riding gang of robbers, causing havoc in the city with their highly organised and skillfully executed bank robberies. When the case is handed over to ACP Jai Dixit, a competent police officer, he takes the help of a local thief, Ali and indulges in a cat and mouse chase to put the crafty kingpin, Kabir, behind bars.

title: Muscle Beach Party
description: Everyone's favorite surfing couple, Frankie and Annette, return for this second BEACH PARTY movie in which the gang finds the beach invaded by the owner of a new gym and his stable of bodybuilders...

title: One of the Good Ones
description: When recovering addict and hopeless romantic JJ meets Sammy on a dating app, so many sparks fly that he decides to drop out of rehab to spend his last three days in town touring Hollywood with the girl of his dreams.

title: Outlaw's Son
description: The deserted son of an outlaw gets on the town's bad side after killing a local banker, and years later tries to fit into society by becoming a deputy marshal.

title: Penny Land
description: A young man drifts through life dreaming about striking it rich by betting on the shady world of penny stocks. As his dream becomes an obsession, he creates a stock scheme that could destroy himself and everyone around him.

title: Sold
description: Young Lakshmi used to live a peaceful life in a village in Nepal, but after a monsoon destroys her family's rice paddy, Lakshmi is trafficked to a brothel in India, where she must endure unspeakable evils while secretly planning her escape.

title: The Black Emperor of Broadway
description: Based on a true story, Charles S. Gilpin was the first African-American in a leading role in a stage play during a time where roles of color were previously played by white men in blackface. As Gilpin rose to fame and recognition, tensions were high between he and playwright Eugene O'Neill which ultimately lead to parting ways, though his acclaimed performance has changed Broadway forever.

title: The Legend of Sarila
description: This is the story of a voyage of initiation in which three young Inuit go in search of a promised land. It is also the story of a fight to the death between two shamans, the young Markussi and the aged Killiq, who feels that his power is threatened. An inspirational tale that uses authentic settings and indigenous mythology in order to capture the world of the Great White North.

title: The Strange Woman
description: In 1820s New England beautiful but poor and manipulative Jenny Hager marries rich old man Isaiah Poster but also seduces his son and his company foreman.

title: A League of Ordinary Gentleman
description: Bowling, though never a sport of kings, at one point in time occupied a perfectly respectable place in the pantheon of American sports.

title: Beast of Yucca Flats
description: A defecting Soviet scientist is hit by a nuclear explosion near Yucca Flats and roams around as a beast.

title: Better Days: The Story of UK Rave
description: 'Better Days' documents over 30 years of UK rave culture; from the first wave of illegal free parties to lockdown gatherings during the global pandemic and everything in between. Featuring interviews with Prospa, Sherelle, Orbital, Dance System, TSHA, and more.

title: Bluestone Four Two
description: The men and women of bomb disposal unit Bluestone 42 are back in this poignant comedy.

title: Climate Next
description: An AWS original documentary series that journeys around the world to discover the people, the ideas, and the technologies currently combatting climate change.

title: Hard Luck Love Song
description: A crime thriller love story based on Todd Snider’s song, “Just Like Old Times.” Jesse (Michael Dorman) is a charismatic but down on his luck troubadour making bad decisions in pool halls and cheap motels with Carla (Sophia Bush), an old flame.

title: Hard Luck Love Song (4K UHD)
description: A crime thriller love story based on Todd Snider's song, "Just Like Old Times." Jesse (Michael Dorman) is a charismatic but down on his luck troubadour making bad decisions in pool halls and cheap motels with Carla (Sophia Bush), an old flame.

title: I Take This Oath
description: The trials and tribulations of a group of newly sworn-in police officers.

title: I Want to Live
description: An elderly hunter and a guy, a runaway from prison, accidentally meet in a hunting hut in the Siberian taiga. Near the warm stove, they share with each other about how each one wants to live. But literally on the next day, the life of them both tragically cut short because of the rifle.

title: Mayor Cupcake
description: A hard-working cupcake maker is inadvertently elected mayor of a small town burdened with debt. Uneducated, she relies on her street smarts to clean up the town.

title: My Favorite Five
description: Hailey is a self-proclaimed serial dater who has no interest in marriage, kids or a picket fence. Hailey does however enjoy the company of men, five to be exact. She believes no one man can posses all five of her most coveted qualities. Soon Hailey meets Christopher, who has no interest in her. As the five fall from the flock one by one, Hailey has to cross lines to get the one man who has it all.

title: Smashers - Cartoons for Kids
description: Welcome to the Smashers Smash Zone, where smashers are pitted against each other in a tough competition. Who's the going to be crowned the king?

title: The Big Chance
description: Frankie, a young prizefighter, wins a fixed boxing match as part of a crime boss's plan to have him build up a following and then have him throw a championship fight.

title: The House of Cards Trilogy
description: The Final Cut. The concluding part to the original House of Cards serial. Francis Urquhart, who is still Prime Minister, becomes heavily involved in a foreign war over oil trading. Can he remain invincible as the highly charged political events start spiraling out of his control?

title: The Kids in the Hall
description: The iconic Canadian sketch comedy troupe The Kids in the Hall return with a new season of their ground-breaking sketch series. Starring Dave Foley, Bruce McCulloch, Kevin McDonald, Mark McKinney, and Scott Thompson.

title: The Law Rides Again
description: The Trail Blazers try to quell threats of an Indian uprising in the Arizona territory.

title: The Rainbow Experiment
description: The story takes place in a high school where things spiral out of control when a terrible accident involving a science experiment injures a kid for life.

title: The Royle Family
description: The Royles return with the newlyweds Denise and Dave expecting their first baby.

title: 1,000 Convicts and a Woman
description: After returning from a Boston finishing school, the daughter of British prison governor uses her position to seduce both the guards and inmates forcing them to set a trap to reveal her true nature to her unsuspecting father.

title: A Tattered Web
description: A detective discovers his son-in-law is cheating on his wife. He confronts the other woman and accidentally kills her, then tries to pin the crime on a local derelict.

title: Aces & Eights
description: A cardsharp comes to the aid of a Mexican family.

title: After School
description: September Johnson is the perfect student, full of brains and beauty. But her favorite subject is Michael, an attractive young professor. What September wants to learn from him isn't taught in the classroom. Now the lesson really begins - after school.

title: After the Fox
description: This wildly funny farce gives the comic genius of Peter Sellers free reign as he assumes several wacky personalities in an original script by Neil Simon.

title: Alice Of Wonderland In Paris
description: After Wonderland, Alice dreams of going to Paris. A mouse named Francois, the grandson of Anatole, agrees to take her there if she will tell him her favorite cheese. Along the way they share several stories.

title: Amazing Mr X
description: On the beach one night, Christine Faber thinks she hears her late husband Paul calling out of the surf...then meets a tall dark man, Alexis, who knows about such things. After more ghostly manifestations, Christine and her sister become enmeshed in the eerie artifices of Alexis; but he in turn finds himself manipulated into deeper deviltry than he had in mind...

title: Another Soul
description: With nightmares haunting their daughter Megan, Rob and Susan are at their wit's end. When someone suggests that her soul might be the target of a demon, the family find themselves battling not only for Megan's life, but for their own lives as well.

title: Arizona Whirlwind
description: Hoot Gibson and the Trailblazers take jobs as telephone linemen to get the goods on a local banker who is the chief of a band of counterfeiters.

title: Attack Of The Giant Leeches
description: After local-moonshine trapper Lem Sawyer sees a giant creature, people start disappearing. While searching for illegal traps Steve Benton and Nan Greyson, his girl-friend find Lem dying with giant sucker wounds on his body.

title: Baby Cat
description: Baby Cat, a sultry tease and top Paris fashion model, enters this lavish lifestyle and plans an elaborate kidnapping.

title: Bachelor Games
description: A group of friends on a stag weekend in the mountains of Argentina are picked off by a dark force called "The Hunter", but all is not what it seems.

title: Bar 20 Justice
description: Outlaw miners have been stealing ore from Ann Dennis' mine. Hoppy spends much of his time running around in the mine shafts tracking down the crooks.

title: Bat People
description: When Dr. John Beck and his wife Cathy fall into an underground cave, a huge bat bites the doctor. Soon, the doctor begins to mutate into a horrible, blood-sucking monster. Dr. Beck embarks on a killing spree to conceal what he's become.

title: Beachhead
description: Marines are sent to survey a Japanese mine location.

title: Beast from Haunted Cave
description: A group of gold thieves pull of a heist and flee into the snowy wilderness, only to be pursued by a horrible, spider-like monster.

title: Beautiful Ones, The
description: In the midst of a turf war, a mob family shylock falls in love with the daughter of his rival crime-family. Refusing to fall to the same fate as Romeo and Juliet, he must use his unique skills to rescue her from the people he once called brothers.

title: Beauty And The Beast (1962)
description: Among lavish period costumes and opulent sets, this fabulous fairy tale – about a lovely maiden who helps a beast transform into a handsome prince – comes brilliantly to life.

title: Bill Hicks: One Night Stand
description: It's a wild night in 1989 of raucous fun as Bill Hicks shows us his unique view on smoking cigarettes, smoking pot, drinking, sex, advertising, and music.

title: Black Dragons
description: A cabal of American industrialists, all fifth-columnists intent on sabotaging the war effort, are methodically murdered by the malevolent Monsieur Colomb.

title: Blood Bath (1966)
description: A succession of beautiful girls mysteriously disappear, shocking the city of Venice, California. Behind the disappearances is a modern-day vampire who, we learn, is the famous artist Sordi, reincarnation of a vampire ancestor.

title: Blowing Up Right Now
description: Graphic artist Shep and his longtime girlfriend Mandy are just in the midst of a devastating breakup when the unthinkable happens: a nuclear missile heading for their neighborhood. Forced to barricade together, their breakup takes the backseat.

title: Border Patrol
description: When three Texas Rangers try to investigate kidnapped Mexicans being used as forced labor in the mines of Silver Bullet, they are framed for murder by the town's corrupt sheriff.

title: Borderline (1950)
description: Two undercover agents infiltrate a drug-smuggling ring in Mexico, but neither is aware of the other's identity.

title: Boy Takes Girl
description: When a young girl falls in love for the first time, it leaves her with a memory she'll cherish for the rest of her life. This is a story of the tender emotions of a child who discovers the excitement, and the pain, of what it's like to fall in love.

title: Brass
description: The Chief of Detectives of the New York Police Department, is a tough cop who has worked his way up the ladder from being on a beat.

title: Break Night
description: A Safecracker has one night to repay a debt before he can leave town, all the while trying to win back the woman he left behind, as well as duck a crooked police officer.

title: Brightest Star
description: After the heartbreaking end of his first love, a recent college graduate sets out to win back the girl of his dreams only to discover a greater journey awaits him.

title: Broadway to Cheyenne (1932)
description: A cowboy detective goes up against a gang of big-city thugs trying to set up a protection racket out west.

title: Broken Mile
description: Drug addict Shaun awakens in a stupor to find that the girl he's with is dead. Panicked, Shaun flees the scene without calling for an ambulance, but the girl's boyfriend is hot on his trail - upset and possibly violent.

title: Bush Pilot
description: Red North is getting by as a reliable small-time bush pilot in Canada's north. But Red's vindicative half-brother Paul Gerard decides to relocate his bush pilot business to the same lake, cutting into Red's routes.

title: By Any Means
description: A C-list celebrity gets kidnapped and held hostage after a night-club appearance. When the police interrogate the man she accuses, they question whether she's after justice or a front-page story.

title: C.H.O.M.P.S.
description: A Disneyesque comedy about a small-town security systems company that is saved from bankruptcy when a young engineer designs a computer- controlled watchdog.

title: C.O.G.
description: Armed with books, an Ivy League education, and a strong conviction of atheism, Samuel heads out to Oregon to work on an apple farm. Out of his element, he finds his lifestyle picked apart by religious locals and untrustworthy coworkers.

title: Call Me Bwana
description: Laugh along with this breezy comedy as Bob Hope heads for the African Jungle where he finds himself on an outrageous safari with elephants, hippos, and...spies? Co-stars Anita Ekberg and Edie Adams.

title: Callie and Son
description: Callie was a teenage mother in trouble. Fresh out of the delivery room, her son was taken from her and sold on the black-market. Vowing to find him some day, this is her story.

title: Cassanova Was A Woman
description: Cassanova Canto is a 5'7", blonde, blue-eyed Cuban-American struggling actor who has fallen in love with a woman, while still married to her husband. Throw in a famous Spanish soap star mother, a homophobic sister, a yogi therapist, and a naked guy, and her dilemma takes a twist. Can you be a free-spirited, sexually fluid, pansexual, bisexual, metrosexual, monogamist and...also be Latin?

title: Colorado
description: Trouble in Colorado is tying up Union troops needed back east during the Civil War and Lieut. Burke is sent to investigate. Macklin and his gang are causing the problems and Capt. Mason joins them.

title: Colorado Sundown (1952)
description: Rancher helps a friend claim a spread he's inherited, only to get involved in his murder.

title: Crazy Enough
description: Identical twins separated at birth. One a prominent psychiatrist, the other a life long mental patient. When the doctor gets called to his brothers institution, fate intervenes and the brothers swap places.

title: CTRL
description: A reclusive programmer, his sister and her new boyfriend are held hostage by a rapidly evolving computer virus.

title: Cul-De-Sac
description: A hermit lives with his nymphomaniac wife in a large dank castle on a small island off the coast of England. Two escaped criminals make their way to the castle and terrorize the couple. Directed by Roman Polanski.

title: Cycle Savages
description: The crazed leader of a motorcycle gang is displeased when an artist opens his sketch pad and reveals "in-the-buff" poses of the biker's girlfriend. Later, the gang leader tracks down the artist...

title: Dangerously Close
description: A gifted student transfers to an elite high school and is recruited by a secret fraternity. When the bodies of students start appearing in the nearby woods, the new boy must find the courage to reveal his horrible secret.

title: Daughter of the Tong
description: A detective matches wits with the female leader of an Oriental crime ring.

title: Devil Riders
description: A crooked lawyer and his gang are trying to steal some government land meant for a stagecoach company. The company hires a cowboy to stop them.

title: Dick Tracy vs. Cueball
description: Evil Cueball abducts Dick Tracy's girlfriend!

title: Dishonored Lady
description: Madeleine Damien is the fashion editor of a slick Manhattan magazine by day and a lively party girl by night. Unfortunately, the pressures of her job, including kowtowing to a hefty advertiser are driving her to a breakdown.

title: Do You Know Me?
description: When Ellie Carter discovers that her real identity is that of a girl gone missing twenty years before, she begins to doubt everything she thought was real. But putting the pieces of her twisting life together proves a dangerous option.

title: Double Cross
description: A cop goes undercover to bust a crime ring.

title: East Side Kids
description: East Side Kids help a pal acused of murder.

title: Easy Money
description: Dan Adams resigns his position as prosecutor on the district attorney's staff and sets out to clean up a gang of fake-accident racketeers.

title: Face Of Evil (1996)
description: A psychopathic young woman who assumes the identity of her murder victims, pretends to be a college freshman and seduces the wealthy widowed father of her roommate.

title: Family Enforcer
description: Neighborhood kid goes to work for the Mafia as a debt collector.

title: Fear in the Night (1947)
description: A man dreams he committed murder, then begins to suspect it was real.

title: Fighting Renegade
description: A government agent falsely accused of murdering a professor takes the identity of "The Puma", a Mexican vigilante leader, to hide his real identity and find the actual killers.

title: Filthy McNastiest
description: The demonic D'artagnan grants Clavell's desire to satisfy his lover in one area where he's coming up "short" with hilariously over-the-top consequences, proving yet again that the female is indeed the deadliest of the species!

title: Fireball 500
description: Melodrama about stock car racing has driver Frankie Avalon getting mixed up with moonshiners when he pauses in a southern town to do some racing.

title: Fishbowl California
description: Pushing thirty with no direction, Rodney is facing homelessness. When he winds up in the home of a hardened, ailing widow, the pair become an unlikely mother and son figure, creating family for each other over time.

title: Flying Wild
description: The East Side Kids uncover a group of spies while working in an airfield during World War II.

title: Fugitive Valley
description: The Range Busters have a plan to get into the outlaw's hideout in Fugitive Valley. The Sheriff puts Crash and Langdon in jail together and then has Dusty break them out.

title: Funniest Man in the World, The
description: From the most loved comedian ever, a carefully selected presentation of his most memorable screen moments. Charlie Chaplin, the comic genius, can finally be shared again. A film that is timeless, touching and hilarious, from the all-time master.

title: Fury on Wheels
description: A young hillbilly from Appalachia moves to Florida. Too lazy to get a job, he cons people into drag racing against him. He catches the eye of the head of a driving team, who quickly signs him up.

title: Gas-s-s-s
description: A mysterious gas released from an Alaskan defense plant kills everyone on Earth over the age of 25. The power of the world is thus thrust into the hands of young people.

title: Ghost Town
description: A gunrunner, a newsman, his fiancee and other travelers reveal flaws during an Indian attack.

title: Ginger In the Morning
description: An attractive young hitchhiker named Ginger meets and and takes up with a lonely, middle-aged advertising executive who is recently divorced. He is inspired by her free-spirited independence while she is drawn to his old-fashioned romanticism.

title: Go For Broke!
description: Van Johnson stars as an inexperienced leader of a group of Japanese-American soldiers while fighting the Nazis in Europe.

title: Grave Of The Vampire
description: A vampire attacks a couple in a graveyard, brutally raping the woman. The child born feeds only on the blood of his mother, until she dies from anemia. As the child grows into adulthood, he curses his heritage.

title: Great St. Louis Bank Robbery
description: A gang's plans for a St. Louis bank robbery are complicated when the sister of one of the thieves starts voicing her well-founded suspicions.

title: Greyfriars Bobby
description: Following his death, Constable John Gray's loyal terrier Bobby is entrusted to Ewan, a shy young man whom Gray had taken under his wing. Despite their friendship, Bobby refuses to leave his master's side.

title: Guess What We Learned In School (1970)
description: Parents in a small, conservative community don't think that the sex drive is a normal thing for children to experience. So much so, that they label education in that regard as a communist plot.

title: Guest in the House
description: A young manipulative woman moves in with her fiances family and turns a happy household against itself.

title: Gun Fever
description: Two men set out to avenge a massacre which killed the parents of one of them. The killers: a band of Indians led by a white renegade. Unknown to the orphaned pursuer – his partner is one of the killers!

title: Hands Across the Border (1944)
description: Horse breeders Adams and Brock are vying for the Army contract. When Adams is killed trying to ride his horse, Roy saves the horse from being shot. He trains him and then plans to ride him in the race to win the contract.

title: Hank and Mike
description: Two blue-collar Easter Bunnies get fired and try their hand at an assortment of odd jobs, failing at each.

title: Happy Ending
description: Stunning performances from an all-star cast, including Jean Simmons, John Forsythe and Shirley Jones, highlight this hard-hitting and deeply personal look at marriage – and other fairy tales.

title: He Walked By Night
description: This film-noir piece, told in semi-documentary style, follows police on the hunt for a resourceful criminal who shoots and kills a cop.

title: Hell Squad
description: Their cover is Las Vegas showgirls, but don't let that fool you! They are highly trained commandos on a secret mission to the Middle East that takes them behind the lines and under the sheets.

title: Here We Go Round the Mulberry Bush
description: A high-school dropout, obsessed with sex, is determined to lose his virginity.

title: Hidden Gold
description: Hoppy and Lucky have been called in to investigate a series of stage holdups.

title: Hold That Woman!
description: A skip tracer repossesses a small radio from a deadbeat who's skipped payments. What he doesn't know is that a gang has stashed stolen diamonds inside the radio, and they start hunting for him.

title: Home In Oklahoma
description: Roy edits a small town newspaper. A rancher is murdered, and his fortune is inherited by a young boy. Editor Roy, with the assistance (?) of big city reporter Dale, brings the killers to justice.

title: Home Sweet Home
description: When a young married couple comes home from a date night to discover they've become trapped inside their own house by a deranged, methodical killer, the husband and wife must do whatever it takes to survive his twisted game.

title: House Of Secrets
description: Two men stumble into an old mansion, and get involved with a crazed scientist, torture chambers and sinister medical experiments.

title: Huk
description: Academy Award-winning screenwriter Stirling Sillipant (IN THE HEAT OF THE NIGHT) created this violent drama about a young plantation owner (George Montgomery) who faces rampaging former Filipino Freedom Fighters.

title: Hunchback of Notre Dame (1923)
description: In fifteenth century Paris, the brother of the archdeacon plots with the gypsy king to foment a peasant revolt. Meanwhile, a freakish hunchback falls in love with the gypsy queen.

title: I'Ll Take Sweden
description: Bob Hope will do almost anything to keep his impressionable teenage daughter (Tuesday Weld) from marrying her lazy boyfriend (Frankie Avalon), even if it means moving to Sweden.

title: If It's Tuesday This Must Be Belgium
description: This story follows the adventures of a group of American tourists taking an eighteen-day guided bus tour of nine European countries.

title: In The Custody Of Strangers
description: A teenage delinquent who goes on a drunken joyride is left in jail overnight by his parents in the hope that he might learn a lesson from it.

title: International Crime
description: Lamont Cranston (Rod La Rocque), amateur criminologist and detective, with a daily radio program, sponsored by the Daily Classic newspaper, has developed a friendly feud that sometimes ...

title: Invasion of the Bee Girls
description: A special state investigator is sent to a small California town to investigate the mysterious death of a physicist. More deaths occur and it soon appears that the victims – all male – are dying from excessive sexual activity.

title: Isolani
description: When single teen mother Isla Corrie witnesses the murder of a police informant, she becomes a pawn in a dangerous game, forced to outwit an ambitious prosecutor, a corrupt detective and a desperate killer to protect her son and start a new life.

title: It Takes Two
description: Forty-eight hours before his wedding, Travis is getting cold feet – and all it takes is a fast car and a faster woman to make him forget his previous engagement in this racy, non-stop comedy.

title: It's a Revolution, Mother
description: This documentary depicts the wild swinging youth scene of the turbulent 60's, with indepth footage of hippies doing a protest march against the Vietnam war in Washington, D.C.,

title: Jive Turkey
description: A numbers king pin tries to stay in business as the mafia and police close in around him.

title: Joyride
description: Three fun-loving teenagers decide to leave their dull jobs in California and head north to Alaska'a pipeline in search of romance and adventure.

title: Kansas City Confidential
description: An ex GI is framed for an armed robbery, put into jail and tortured. When they can't prove it was him, he goes on a quest to find the culprits and enters into the murky underworld of killers and corrupt policemen.

title: Kansas Pacific
description: With the Civil War about to begin, Southern saboteurs attack frontier railroad construction.

title: King Of The Newsboys
description: A poor young man's girlfriend leaves him for a gangster.

title: Kingdom of War, Part 2
description: Part 2 portrays Naresuan as a young adult prince, already a formidable military strategist, as he leads his army on exploits against breakaway kingdoms.

title: Legend of Two Sisters In the Chaos
description: During the Later Zhou Dynasty, the Fu family was the focus of world attention to the well-known prophecy given to Fu Yan Qing that states that one of the daughters of the Fu family would become the future Empress.

title: Lights Of Old Santa Fe
description: Rival rodeos are operated by good guy Gabby and bad guy Richard Powers. Dale is trying to choose between them, aided ultimately by Roy and the Sons of the Pioneers (who are radio singers).

title: Lisa
description: A 14-year-old, chafing at restrictions imposed by her single mother, makes phone calls to strange, handsome men – unaware that one of them is a murderer who preys on single women.

title: Lucky Texan
description: An older rancher and a young miner strike it lucky in the gold fields, and go to the Assay Office to report their claim. However, greedy assayers follow them back to the claim, shoot the rancher and frame the miner for murder.

title: Lumberjack
description: Julie's husband has been murdered and land agents want her to sign away her property rights. Hoppy warns against this but she does so anyway. It looks as though she will be unable to deliver the timber in her agreement.

title: Mad Monster (1942)
description: A mad scientist changes his simple-minded handyman into a werewolf in order to prove his supposedly crazy scientific theories - and exact revenge.

title: Mambo
description: Silvana Mangano (a very lovely & sexy voiced actress) plays a young, poor Venetian woman, Giovanna Masetti. She is struggling with an difficult life as a shop assistant when one day a young count Enrico sees her in the glass shop where she works.

title: Mind and Machine
description: Set in 2024 where humanoid robots are common in society, the mob reprograms a female android to think and feel so they can use it as a contract killer.

title: Miss Nobody
description: Sarah Jane McKinney is a mild-mannered secretary for a big pharmaceutical company looking for love, until she discovers her talent for murder. As the killings continue, Jane starts to ascend the corporate ladder.

title: Mouse On The Moon
description: Joy in the impoverished Duchy of Grand Fenwick...their locally produced (undrinkable) wine works splendidly as rocket fuel. Their mission: to prove the case by reaching the moon before the Americans or the Russians.

title: Mr. Wise Guy
description: Sent to reform school after getting into trouble, the East Side Kids have to escape and help find the real killer responsible for the murder that has been unfairly blamed on Danny's brother.

title: Mutiny
description: Early in the War of 1812, Captain James Marshall is commissioned to run the British blockade and fetch an unofficial war loan from France.

title: Nabonga Gorilla
description: When a treasure hunter seeks a downed airplane in the jungles of Africa, he encounters one of the passenger's young daughter, now fully grown, and with a gorilla protector.

title: New Year's Evil
description: Lonely women wanting to celebrate New Year's Eve become easy prey for a maniacal murdering misogynist whose New Year's resolution is to kill women at every stroke of midnight.

title: Newly Single
description: Astor William Stevenson is on the verge of a big step in his career, but when his girlfriend leaves him, insecurities boil to the surface and he transforms into a wrecking ball on a stream of darkly comedic dates and misguided romantic pursuits.

title: Number One of the Secret Service
description: Men in high places of high finance are being murdered. Agent Number One of the Secret Service is called in by his superior and ordered to put a stop to it.

title: Outlaw Trail
description: The Trail Blazers go to the aid of ranchers who are being oppressed by a town boss and his henchmen.

title: Outlaws Of Sonora
description: Dude's gang captures Stony and seeing the resemblance, Dude poses as Stony. Wanted for the robberies and murder committed by Dude, a wounded Stony escapes.

title: Paradise Canyon
description: Sent to find counterfeiters, John Wyatt joins Doc Carter's medicine show.

title: Parlor Bedroom and Bath
description: A man tries passing off a socially awkward fellow as a Casanova in the hopes of marrying off his would be sister-in-law.

title: Pocket Money
description: In the town of Thiers, summer of 1976, teachers and parents give their children skills, love, and attention.

title: Premature Burial
description: Ray Milland is obsessed with the idea that he will be buried while in a state of catalepsy. He marries a woman who promises to cure him with love. His fears become real.

title: Quest for the Mighty Sword
description: Once upon a time a god gave a mighty sword to the king of Aquiles to bring justice to his people. Now he wants it back - but the king rather gives his life than the sword.

title: Raasi
description: Kumar, a young man, falls in love with Meena, his uncle's daughter. Complications come to light when he is unable to shell out enough money for an important occasion.

title: Racing Scene
description: The story of James Garner's year with his racing team, from the time he bought the car, and assembled his team through Mexico, England, Florida and Canada.

title: Rag Doll
description: Nora is the one who works overtime, helps out her family by all means, and leaves little for herself. She takes out life's hardships at the local mixed martial arts gym, but what happens when that violence extends outside of the gym?

title: Record City
description: Lighthearted comedy chronicling the exploits of the employees at a record store.

title: Return To Treasure Island
description: A descendant of Jim Hawkins visits Treasure Island with a priceless map.

title: Revolt of the Zombies
description: An international expedition is sent into Cambodia to destroy an ancient formula that turns men into zombies.

title: Riders of Destiny
description: Bad guy Kincaid controls the local water supply and plans to do in the other ranchers. Government agent Saunders shows up undercover to do in Kincaid and win the heart of one of his victims Fay Denton.

title: Sacrificed
description: WARNING: Subject matter. After the FBI informs Tom Hawkins that his son was slain in a cult sacrifice, he carves a bloody trail of revenge hell-bent on annihilating anyone involved - regardless of what side of the law they're on.

title: Schizoid
description: FROM 1980: A newspaper columnist starts receiving threats from a mysterious person. At the same time, the female members of her psychiatrist's therapy group are being murdered one by one-by a scissor-wielding maniac.

title: Sisters of Death
description: During an all-girl secret society initiation, one of the new members is killed playing Russian Roulette. Many years later the survivors are invited for a reunion to a lavish estate.

title: Ski Party
description: Get your skis on and keep your tips up for this sin-sational snow romp with the "Beach Party" gang! Frankie Avalon and Dwayne Hickman star as two would-be snow studs who go undercover as a couple of snow bunnies to find out what girls want from men!

title: Song Of Texas
description: A man of no worth brags to his daughter back East that he is rich and owns a big ranch. When she decides to pay a visit to her father, Roy and his buddies agree to pretend that the poor man is the owner of the ranch.

title: South Of Santa Fe
description: New Mexico is the scene of undeveloped gold mines and kidnapping. Modern elements include tommy guns, an airplane, two-way radios, fast cars, and big city gangsters.

title: Springtime in the Rockies
description: Ranch owner Sandra, fresh from animal husbandry school, brings a flock of sheep into cattle country. The local ranchers don't like it, and ranch foreman Gene must deal with it.

title: Steel Sharks
description: When a US submarine is seized by terrorists, a team of Navy SEALS called the Steel Sharks are sent to rescue it. But when their attempt fails, the Steel Sharks and the captives they were called to save must wage a silent war beneath the waves.

title: Stranger Who Looks Like Me
description: In this 1974 TV movie, Meredith Baxter and Beau Bridges portray adult adoptees, desirous of meeting their natural parents. Through the auspices of a tracing agency, Baxter, Bridges and several others locate their actual mothers.

title: Street People
description: A Mafia chief imports a cross from Sicily for a cathedral, but it contains a cache of pure heroin. He denies any involvement, and an attorney is brought in to solve the mystery.

title: Submarine Alert
description: Nazi spies use a stolen shortwave transmitter prototype to broadcast top secret shipping info to an offshore Japanese sub. To nab the spy ring, the Government has the West Coast's top radio engineers fired and shadowed.

title: Sunlight Jr.
description: A Florida couple deals with an unexpected pregnancy while holding minimum wage jobs.

title: Terror At London Bridge
description: Jack the Ripper is mystically resurrected in contemporary Arizona and goes on a killing spree in the British-style tourist trap. Only one man suspects that this is more than the work of a serial-killer.

title: Thamizh
description: Thamizh, a brave youth, looks forward to working with his brother in Kuwait. Meanwhile, circumstances force him to clash with some gangsters which earn him Periyavar's wrath.

title: That Brennan Girl
description: A feisty girl has bad luck in this comedy. (1946)

title: That Gang Of Mine
description: A street kid has dreams of becoming a jockey. He gets his chance when he and his gang discover a poor old man who has a championship race horse.

title: The Assisi Underground
description: This gripping story of the crucial work done by the people of Assisi to rescue hundreds of Italian Jews from Nazi execution during their occupation of Italy in 1943.

title: The Barn
description: A serial killer strikes Sugar Grove, Virginia. A rising journalist comes to town to cover the story : her investigation will soon lead her to the town's darkest secret, at her own risks.

title: The Bet
description: A woman makes a bet with her husband that she can get the next man she sees to propose to her.

title: The Brass Legend
description: An honest sheriff attempts to save an 11-year-old boy who helped him capture a notorious killer.

title: The Choppers
description: A gang of teenage delinquents terrorize a small community by stealing cars and stripping them for parts, then selling the parts to a crooked junkyard owner.

title: The Eclipse
description: In a seaside Irish town, a widower sparks with a visiting horror novelist while he also begins to believe he is seeing ghosts.

title: The Fat Spy
description: Eccentrics search for the fountain of youth.

title: The Giant Gila Monster
description: A giant lizard terrorizes a rural Texas community with a heroic teenager attempting to destroy the creature.

title: The Gorilla
description: When a wealthy man (Atwill) is threatened by a killer known as The Gorilla, he hires the Ritz Brothers to investigate. A real escaped gorilla shows up at the mansion just as the investigators arrive.

title: The Gridiron
description: A man who fails at everything he attempts puts all of his efforts into forming an American football team in a country dominated by soccer.

title: The Incantation
description: A young American girl has a chance of a lifetime to visit her ancestors castle in the south of France, only to find that her family is hiding deep, dark secrets about their nefarious past.

title: The Joe Louis Story
description: The life and career of Heavyweight Champion Joe Louis, who held the title for 12 years – longer than any other boxer in history – and who had to not only battle opponents inside the ring and racism outside it.

title: The Klansman
description: A local Sheriff tries to keep the peace as racial strife hits his small Alabama town as tensions boil over when a black man is accused of raping a white woman.

title: The Lady Refuses
description: A wealthy London nobleman hires a pretty but poor young girl to distract his playboy son from marrying a golddigger.

title: The Last King [English Subtitled]
description: Set in the Middle Ages, in the midst of a great civil war. A monarch is murdered. His soldiers escape with the infant heir to the throne. The warriors risk their life to shepherd him across snowy mountains to claim his rightful place on the throne.

title: The Love Flower
description: A man murders his wife's lovers, escapes with his daughter to the South Pacific. A detective pursues him, joined by a young man who eventually falls in love with the daughter.

title: The Midnighters
description: An aging safe-cracker recently released from prison is asked to put his old skills to use and risk his freedom to save his son's life.

title: The Old Barn Dance
description: ADVENTURE WITH MUSIC! THE SCREEN'S ACE COWBOY IN THE SNAPPIEST, MOST EXCITING WESTERN YET! Gene Autry and Frog Millhouse are horse traders who run into trouble when an unscrupulous tractor company starts selling the modern machines to farmers. To make money, Gene and his cowboy band perform on a radio station, only to be tricked into endorsing the tractors!

title: The Outlaw
description: This movie follows the friendship of Billy and fellow outlaw Doc Holliday, as they both pursue the affections of Holliday's girlfriend, Rio while being chased through the desert by Sheriff Pat McGarrett and his posse.

title: The Phantom Of 42Nd Street
description: A theatre critic (Dave O'Brien) teams up with a cop (Jack Mulhall) to investigate the murder of a Broadway actor.

title: The Pickle Recipe
description: Desperate for cash, a down on his luck party emcee is corrupted by his shameless uncle to steal his grandmother's top secret pickle recipe.

title: The Poughkeepsie Tapes
description: After a decade-long crime spree conducted under the radar of law enforcement, a killer left behind the most disturbing collection of evidence homicide detectives had ever seen - hundreds of homemade videos that chronicled his crimes!

title: The Revolt of the Slaves
description: In this biblical action-adventure, set during the waning years of the Roman Empire, Fabiola (Rhonda Fleming), the beautiful daughter of a wealthy patrician, falls in love with a Christian slave, Vibio (Lang Jeffries).

title: The Unfolding
description: A researcher and his girlfriend travel to the legendary wilds of Dartmoor to investigate a centuries old building with a mysterious past. As their investigation continues, they find themselves drawn into a mortal confrontation with pure evil.

title: The Yes Men
description: A "genderless, loose-knit association of some three hundred impostors worldwide," the Yes Men perpetrate an elegant form of culture jamming that has duped accountants in Sydney, professors in Tampere and lawyers in Salzburg.

title: Three Kinds of Heat
description: Special Asian Affairs Agent Elliot Cromwell joins forces with a stunning New York City policewoman and a beautiful investigator from Interpol. The three of them fuse together into one hot team as they try to crack open an international drug ring.

title: Tim Allen: ReWires America
description: Tim Allen grunts, he burps, he soups up his lawnmower and he's damn proud of it! Filled with family bits as well as the stuff we've come to love him for: tools, engine and cars. In this 1991 special, we see the Tim Allen we grew to love.

title: Tom Brown's School Days
description: A young boy starts at Rugby boarding school. He is tormented by Flashman, the school bully.

title: Too Cold To Swim
description: A man crossing Maine at the end of a solo cross country bicycle trip strikes up a friendship with an ex-Marine and his sister. At the same time he reconnects with his estranged father and finds himself forced to make an irrevocable decision.

title: Topper Returns
description: The spirit of a dead girl haunts Topper. Topper sets out to solve her murder.

title: Treasure of San Lucas
description: An attractive college coed gets involved priceless pre-Columbian artifacts, drug deals, and a romance with an alleged attorney. The two of them team up to double-cross the mob in this fascinating, action-filled adventure.

title: Underground
description: An American intelligence agent attempts to kidnap a top Nazi general.

title: Up In The Cellar
description: A college student loses a scholarship but tries to get even with the president by seducing his wife, daughter and his mistress.

title: Virginia's Run
description: Following the death of her mother in a horseback riding accident, 13-year-old Virginia defies her father's orders and sneaks out each night to ride a foal named Stormy.

title: Voyage Into Space
description: A little Japanese boy, Johnny Sokko, and his giant flying robot prevent the monster Dracolon from destroying Tokyo.

title: Where's Chicky? - Around the World Pt.3
description: Nobody knows where Chicky is exactly, we just know he is cute and deeply naïve. In this compilation, follow Chicky as he visits some of the most recognizable landmarks all around the world!

title: Wizard of Loneliness, The
description: Twelve year old Wendell is a confirmed cynic, sent to his grandparents Vermont farm during World War II. His only desire is to steal enough money to run away, until his loving grandparents, and young Aunt Sybil involve him in their lives.

title: Woman on the Run
description: A man goes into hiding after witnessing a gangland execution.

title: Women and Sometimes Men
description: Briefly engaged, Sara decides to call off her marriage. She had an experience with a woman in college and wants that feeling again, without giving up men.

title: 22 Chaser
description: Ben Dankert is one of Toronto's last decent tow truck divers, but when his family falls into financial trouble, he begins a desperate quest to become king of the road and provide for his struggling family.

title: 3 Hours Till Dead
description: When a soldier's brother gets attacked by an infected farmer, he morphs into a rabid animal and lives for exactly three hours. Quickly realizing the danger they're in, the soldier and his friends must try to outlive the legions of the infected.

title: 96 Souls
description: On the verge of losing both his funding and his status, a university research scientist has a lab accident, giving him the ability to see people's true intentions, which makes his situation even worse.

title: Adult Interference
description: After being sentenced to 90 days of house arrest, Bo befriends the awkward kid across the street to teach him how to play football. Their unlikely friendship teaches them both about what it means to be a man.

title: Age Out
description: Age Out is a passionate portrait of youth set in Waco, Texas. Forced out of foster care at age 18, Richie Wincott (Tye Sheridan) collides with the perils and temptations of a life apart. Becoming a prime suspect in a botched robbery, he discovers an impossible love in an unlikely friend. Age Out is a humane story about love, loss, wrongdoing, and redemption.

title: Alex & the List
description: Dog trainer Alex decides to propose to his girlfriend Katherine, but is blindsided when she gives him a to-do list of "improvements" that she would like him to work on that will make them the ideal couple.

title: Alienate
description: To give his wife some space at the end of their marriage, David departs on a business trip. While separated, the Earth begins falling to an alien invasion, and he must fight to return to whatever is left of his home.

title: All About the Money
description: Two best friends are convinced by a third to take a vacation, but an insane adventure ensues when the two friends find out that his real intentions are to track down America's most wanted drug dealer and claim the $25M bounty on his head.

title: All At Once
description: A young up-and-coming artist living in New York City accepts guardianship of his best friends' daughters after they lose their lives during 9/11. Eleven years later he returns to his hometown, Buffalo, to raise the "non-traditional" family.

title: Almost Adults
description: Lifelong best friends Cassie and Mackenzie struggle with what to do when growing up means growing apart, as they find themselves on separate journeys: one exploring her newfound sexuality, the other breaking up with a long term boyfriend.

title: Almost Friends
description: Once a promising chef, Charlie is now an unmotivated guy in his mid-20s, living at home with his mom. But when he meets his dream girl and his estranged father returns, Charlie's life heads off in a whole new direction.

title: Altered Hours
description: An insomniac's black market sleep aid sends his mind one day into the future where he is suspected of abducting a girl he has not met yet.

title: Always Watching: A Marble Hornets Story
description: When a local news team finds a box of video tapes while investigating a man's mysterious disappearance, they begin to suffer the same fate as the family who recorded them - haunted and tormented by a faceless figure in a dark suit.

title: Amanda & Jack Go Glamping
description: Jack and his wife Amanda book an isolated glamping retreat in hopes of saving their marriage, only to discover their private getaway is more crowded than expected. They are forced to dive into a comedic exploration of love, failure, and donkeys.

title: Ambush Bay
description: In 1944, a nine-man Marine patrol secretly lands on a Japanese-held island in order to contact a spy who has important information about General MacArthur's planned invasion of the Philippines.

title: American Exorcist
description: After a century of tragic deaths the infamous skyscraper is reportedly haunted. Georgette Dubois is a professional skeptic hired by Management to debunk those urban legends.

title: Antarctica A Year On Ice
description: This documentary reveals what it is like to live and work at the bottom of the planet, in Antarctica, for a full year from the point of view of the everyday workers who keep the stations running in the harshest place on Earth. Filmed over 15 years, the film features a unique insider's point of view, with unparalleled access, and never before seen stunning footage of the deep Antarctic winters.

title: Anyone Home?
description: A single mother struggling with bipolar disorder take on a job to be the live-in caretaker of an unsold model home in an empty development. The isolation and pressure from the realtor effect her as she begins to entertain dangerous fantasies.

title: Arbor Demon
description: An adventurous married couple and an injured hunter are held captive inside a claustrophobic tent by a supernatural threat. For an unknown reason, the tent has become their only safe haven. Soon tensions rise inside the Arbor Demon and the truth about the attacker is revealed.

title: Asylum Of Fear
description: Hired after two police officers are mysteriously murdered, a team of paranormal investigators find themselves locked inside the abandoned psychiatric hospital. As they work to solve the case, they discover clues about the hospital's horrifying past.

title: At War With The Army with Dean Martin & Jerry Lewis
description: When former business & nightclub partners Dean Martin & Jerry Lewis enlist in the U.S. Army, (in their first starring film ) they have different ambitions. Martin wants to see action rather than the drudgery of his current post. Lewis, who is a klutz, wants to stay out of combat. However, they both have to deal with stern Army personnel while also preparing for an Army variety show. A laugh riot!

title: Baja
description: Four 22 year-olds on a Mexican road trip seem bound for disaster until they, and their trip, are unexpectedly redeemed by a series of miraculous events.

title: Baked in Brooklyn
description: A guy decides to sell weed after losing his job, but things soon go out of hand as demand of business and paranoia starts taking over.

title: Beast Of The Water
description: Upon making a curious discovery that might lead to the fountain of youth, a research group heads out to find it. But when they don't listen to an ominous warning, the group will learn that nature's law has no mercy.

title: Big Sky
description: Mother and daughter, Dee and Hazel (Sedgwick and Thorne) go on a roadtrip to a desert facility to help Hazel deal with her agoraphobia. When gunmen and brothers Jesse and Pru (Grillo and Tveit) attack the pair, Hazel has to battle her fears so she and her mother can survive.

title: Billion Dollar Hobo
description: A helpless klutz bumbles his way through a disaster-filled life. Suddenly he is informed that he is the only living relative of a multimillionaire. In order to take over his wealth, he has to become a hobo.

title: Bitten
description: Jack is a night-shift paramedic who rescues a troubled young woman from the throes of death. When he brings Danika home to mend, he discovers she's a vampire. Otherwise, she's really perfect. But as the victims pile up, Jack questions his own fate.

title: Black Bear
description: At a lake house, a filmmaker plays a calculated game of desire and jealousy in the pursuit of a work of art that blurs the boundaries between autobiography and invention.

title: Bowery at Midnight
description: Kindly soup kitchen operator and professor of criminology Bela Lugosi uses his soup kitchen as a front for a criminal gang who commit a series of daring robberies and murders.

title: Bridal Boot Camp
description: Andy Phillips is preparing for her upcoming wedding with her fiancé, Jordan. However, after chatting with her best friend, Andy starts to question if she has what it takes to make a strong a lasting marriage.

title: Bus Party to Hell
description: When a party bus on its way to Burning Man filled with a bunch of sexy young adults breaks down in the desert and in the middle of a group of Satanic worshipers, all hell breaks loose.

title: Christmas Survival
description: In this heart-warming holiday comedy, sisters Miranda and Lyla come together to spend Christmas at their late parents' dilapidated country house... but ancient sibling rivalries flare-up to sabotage the holiday season.

title: Crazy Famous
description: Bob is an average Joe whose obsession to be famous lands him in a mental hospital. When a patient claims Bin Laden is still alive, Bob escapes with a band of misfits in a last-ditch effort to get Bin Laden and the fame he so deeply desires.

title: Dark Mountain
description: A woman doesn't realize that the man she has just married is a gangster. When she is implicated in a murder he committed, she turns to an ex-boyfriend, who is now a park ranger, for help.

title: Defiant
description: When framed for the murder of the New World's Sovereign Leader, a young soldier must choose whether he can still embrace the New World knowing what he now knows, or if his allegiances have become Defiant.

title: Delinquent
description: 17-year-old Joey grew up idolizing his small-time crook of a father.

title: Desolation
description: After being whisked away to Los Angeles by a handsome Hollywood star, Katie is left alone in his apartment, where strange and scary things begin to happen.

title: Dick Tracy's Dilemma
description: A crime thriller based on the comic strip. There is a series of fifteen murders and the victims are slashed. They are all from different social and economic backgrounds and Dick Tracy is on the trail of the murderer.

title: Dr. Jekyll and Mr. Hyde
description: For more than a century, the tale of Jekyll and Hyde has captivated the world's imagination. In this chilling and diabolically clever reinvention, evil lives again...

title: Driver
description: After the murder of his wife, Helen, Las Vegas police officer Art's attempts to find her killer were in vain. Suspended from the force, he begins to connect the dots between his wife's death and Henry, an Uber driver with a suspicious past.

title: Eight on the Lam
description: A bank teller is suspected of embezzlement and goes on the run with his seven children.

title: Electra Glide In Blue
description: Bored with his highway traffic duties, Arizona motorcycle patrolman John Wintergreen is assigned to Homicide where his polite investigative style irks his macho boss.

title: Enemy Within
description: After crash-landing on the remote Hawaiian island of Ni'ihau, a Japanese pilot is met with courtesy and traditional Hawaiian hospitality from the locals. But when they discover he was part of the recent attack on Pearl Harbor, everything changes.

title: Flight From Ashiya
description: Three rescue pilots must overcome their fears, differences and hatreds as they undertake the dangerous rescue of raft-bound Japanese on storm-tossed seas.

title: Get Christie Love
description: A beautiful policewoman goes undercover to break up a drug ring.

title: Gold
description: Set in the Klondike in 1898, a woman joins a group of German prospectors as they battle the harsh terrain seeking their fortune in gold only to discover they are being stalked by a pair of ruthless killers for reasons unknown.

title: Good Bones
description: Danny O'Brien falls in love with Clare, the sophisticated girl next door, as he tries to navigate the rich and fabulous world of East Hampton power players.

title: Gun Brothers
description: Buster Crabbe and Neville Brand star as brothers on opposite sides of the law. Chad (Crabbe) is a law abiding rancher, while Jubal (Brand) has opted for life as an outlaw.

title: Gun Duel in Durango
description: He is the leader of a notorious gang. He wants to settle down. She says she will marry once he has proved his newfound virtue. His former gang buddies have other ideas and a final showdown gunfight is inevitable.

title: Heavenly Kid
description: A fantasy-comedy about a cocky teen who, in 1968, dies in a fiery car crash (chicken race) and can't get into Heaven – until he makes amends on Earth by helping out a young nerd in 1985.

title: Hell's Belles
description: The $2,000 cycle that was won in a motorbike race is stolen twice, and the winner sets off across the Arizona desert in pursuit of the gang which has the bike...accompanied by the gang leader's former girlfriend.

title: Holiday Breakup
description: A young couple breaks up and faces the prospect of the holidays turning into one long pity party. Their solution: pretend they're still together.

title: Huckleberry Finn
description: Jeff East is young Huck Finn in this song-filled adaptation of Mark Twain's popular novel that follows Huck and runaway slave Jim (Paul Winfield) on an adventurous journey down the Mississippi River.

title: If I Had Wings
description: Seventeen year old Alex Taylor (Richard Harmon) dreams of flying. He also dreams of running for his high school's cross-country track team.

title: In The Aisles
description: An affecting and bittersweet glimpse into the shared connections of a motley group of nightshift workers at a big box store, including the reclusive newbie Christian (Franz Rogowski) and the charming but mysterious Marion (Sandra Hüller). Includes English subtitles-user may need to turn subtitles on.

title: In the Spider's Web
description: Backpacking in the jungles of a India, a team of hikers stumbles upon the village of Karni Mata?home to a native cult of spider worshippers and to Dr. Lecorpus, an American physician who proves just as formidable a fear as the venomous arachnids.

title: Ishq Brandy
description: This New Punjabi Comedy Film of 2014, 'Ishq Brandy', is a masala potboiler which narrates a story of three friends who have a tag line "if you are my friend, I don't need an enemy"...Teji, Gura and Pritam from three different worlds, bound by their respective Ishq, do something under the spell of Brandy that they unknowingly put their Ishq(s) at stak.

title: Jasper, Texas
description: In June of 1998, a stunning crime thrust the town of Jasper, Texas into the spotlight. What happened on that summer evening-the death of black hitchhiker James Byrd, Jr. by three white men- became a flashpoint for the state of race relations in America.

title: Jhoom Barabar Jhoom
description: A crazy love story full of lies, deceits and a complicated quadrangle where each one has to think quickly and dance around each other's emotions

title: Journey to the Center of Time
description: Campy tale about time travel and aliens.

title: KAOS Brief, The
description: Hacked footage reveals mysterious events surrounding the abduction of four teenagers.

title: Kart Racer
description: 14-year-old Watts Davies is a gifted go-kart racer. The death of his mother has left him estranged from his dad. When the town bully tries to keep him out of the upcoming IKF Championships, it spurs Watts and his father to rekindle their relationship.

title: Keep The Lights On
description: In New York City, filmmaker Erik bonds with closeted, bisexual lawyer Paul after a one-night fling. As their relationship evolves and fueled by highs, lows, and dysfunctional patterns, Erik struggles to negotiate his own boundaries while being true to himself. A film about sex, friendship, intimacy and most of all, love.

title: Kids from 62-F
description: A group of kids find classified information from NASA and an object from another Planet and work to get it back to its rightful owners.

title: Killer Movie: Director's Cut
description: In 2008, a reality television crew was dispatched to a small town in North Dakota to cover the story of an underdog high school hockey team on their way to the state finals. One by one, members of the cast and crew went missing. This is their story. This all-new Director's Cut has been completely overhauled for 2021.

title: Lady of Burlesque
description: After one member of their group is murdered, the performers at a burlesque house must work together to find out who the killer is before they strike again.

title: Le Week-End
description: Academy Award winner Jim Broadbent and Lindsay Duncan give exquisite performances as Nick and Meg, a long-married British couple revisiting Paris for the first time since their honeymoon in an attempt to rekindle their relationship.

title: Lord Love A Duck
description: Roddy McDowell, Tuesday Weld, Harvey Korman and Ruth Gordon star in this deliciously offbeat comedy that satirizes 1960s Southern California teen culture.

title: Lost Creek
description: After moving to a new town, 11-year-old Peter and his friend Bill must team up with mysterious new girl Maggie and brave the woods on Halloween to face a monster born from their nightmares.

title: Louise By the Shore
description: On the last day of summer in a small seaside town, an older woman named Louise realizes that the last train has departed without her. She finds herself alone. As the weather turns for the worse, she must rely on her past to help her survive the present.

title: Love Is A Ball
description: Charles Boyer zestfully portrays a (self-appointed) matchmaker on the French Riviera, conducting a lively cast on a slippery road to Romance.

title: Lovesick
description: Matt LeBlanc stars as an eccentric head teacher who goes clinically insane every time he falls for someone. Romantic comedy with Ali Larter and Chevy Chase.

title: Marrowbone
description: Four siblings with their mother move to escape a troubled past. When she dies, they vow to stay together. But when a ghostly presence torments them and a lawyer threatens their pact, the four must stand together or be torn apart forever.

title: Maybe I'll Come Home in the Spring
description: After finding out that the hippie lifestyle isn't as glamorous as the media makes it look, Dennie comes home to find disapproval and judgment at every turn, and her sister Susie wanting to follow in her footsteps.

title: Mesrine: Killer Instinct
description: Mesrine, is a loyal son and soldier back home and living with his parents after serving in the Algerian War. Seduced by the glamour and easy money of 60's Paris, he turns his back on his old life and moves swiftly up the criminal ladder. After pulling off an audacious heist he flees to Canada where the lure of a big payout draws him out of hiding and propels his towards international notoriety.

title: Mikhael
description: When a vengeful man with criminal ties starts hunting down his family, Dr. Mikhael vows to protect them and annihilate his enemy.

title: Monkey Hustle
description: Street hustlers and con-artists are about to be left without a turf or victims if the proposed freeway comes to fruition.

title: Monochrome
description: A disillusioned young woman becomes a serial killer targeting wealthy land-owners, forcing a brilliant detective to use his unusual neurological condition to track her down.

title: Mugguru Monagallu
description: Mugguru Mongallu is a comedy thriller and Srinivasa Reddy is the biggest highlight of the film. It's the story of Three people who are apparently deaf (Srinivas Reddy), dumb (Deekshit Shetty), and blind (Vennela Rama Rao) each, go to the police station with a few clues regarding the murders. Will the police catch the killers?

title: Murder Once Removed
description: A doctor and the wife of one of his wealthy patients hatch a plot to get rid of her husband so they can be together and get his money.

title: Nobody Famous
description: A group of aspiring actors' cottage weekend takes a turn for the worst when one of them finds out they've booked a blockbuster role, and the rest of the group's jealously takes hold where there's no one else around.

title: Noose for a Gunman
description: To save a town from a notorious outlaw, a gunslinger is asked to become marshal.

title: Nowhere Michigan
description: David is fleeing from a murder, a pair of deadly con-men, and is inadvertently toting a bag full of crystal meth and cash with him. On the run, he ends up in a small, frozen, nowhere town in the heart of the Upper Peninsula of Michigan.

title: One Under The Sun
description: An astronaut who survives a disastrous space mission, tries to reunite with her terminally ill daughter but becomes a fugitive when the gov't discovers she's returned to earth with a special gift.

title: Other Side, The
description: It was a groundbreaking device designed to glimpse alternate universes and government commissioned by a brilliant physicist. But the machine malfunctioned on its first presentation, transporting a group of observers into a new dimension.

title: Pig Hag
description: Jodie, a woman in her mid-thirties, struggles with the pressure to find a partner and have children. When she attends a Guns N' Roses concert, she thinks she may have met a potential suitor – until he ghosts on her.

title: Revolt at Fort Laramie
description: At the dawn of the American Civil War, tensions begin to mount between Northern and Southern sympathizers stationed at Fort Laramie in Wyoming.

title: Richard Jeni: Platypus Man
description: Richard Jeni takes the Windy City on a non-stop joyride through American Culture. He cracks into everything from lobsters to love songs in this hour long live performance.

title: Ripped
description: In 1986, two free spirited stoners are catapulted into 2016 after smoking some top secret pot created by the CIA. Now, the balding and overweight protagonists must use their uncomplicated enthusiasm to figure out how to live in the modern world.

title: Ritual
description: During a vacation in the woods, a man tries to find his family, while being hunted by a sadistic killer.

title: Say You Will
description: A recent high school graduate cares for his mother and navigates his first relationship in the wake of his father's suicide.

title: Sea Beast
description: Captain Will McKenna and marine biologist Arden Jaymes discover why the fishing village of Cedar Bay is being depleted of its resources. What's been devouring the fish in the sea has come ashore in search of something more substantial: human flesh.

title: Sex Madness
description: This exploitation film belongs to the social guidance genre of quasi-documentary narratives, which exhort young adults to follow particular moral and social prescriptions related to sexuality and drug use.

title: She
description: A remake of the H. Rider Haggard novel about an immortal queen and her adventures. She is the leader of a nation that treats men as second- class citizens, during post-apocalyptic times.

title: Sioux City
description: Focuses on Jesse Rainfeather Goldman, a young doctor of Native American ancestry raised by an affluent Beverly Hills family.

title: Someone Marry Barry
description: In this hilarious romantic comedy, a trio of childhood friends schemes to find a wife for their socially inappropriate pal Barry (Tyler Labine, "Monsters University"). Their plan completely backfires when his new girlfriend Melanie.

title: Starflight One
description: In this taut, futuristic drama, the maiden voyage of a hypersonic passenger jet becomes a disaster when something goes terribly wrong and it gets stuck in orbit.

title: Steven Tyler: Out On A Limb
description: An intimate portrait of rock icon Steven Tyler as he embraces the challenges of shifting gears, both as a solo performer and in a new genre of music. Uncovering a side of Tyler many fans have never seen before, this inspiring story looks at the passion, drive and search for creative fulfillment that keeps artists pushing boundaries throughout their careers.

title: Stolen Hours
description: Susan Hayward stars as a rich Texas playgirl with no real ambition who meets a young Welsh doctor who sees the despair beneath her indifference – and the illness she's trying to hide.

title: Storage 24
description: With London on lockdown after a military cargo plane crash, four friends are trapped in the Storage 24 facility - a dark maze of endless corridors - with a mysterious predator hunting them one by one.

title: Straight Into Darkness
description: Two American soldiers who want to desert their platoon near the end of WWII find themselves trapped in a crumbling building with a group of orphans trained to kill and surrounded on all sides by Nazi war tanks.

title: Street Warrior
description: War vet Jack Campbell returns to his hometown to find it a capital of corruption. The main attraction is the Gauntlet, a fight club, which has already counted Jack's brother among its casualties. Jack wants revenge-and the plan begins in the Gauntlet.

title: Tales Of Terror
description: Three short stories ("Morella," "The Black Cat," and "The Case of M. Valdemar") based on the works of the master horror writer, Edgar Allan Poe, and feature Vincent Price in the starring role.

title: Terror In The Family
description: Deena Marten (Oscar winner Hillary Swank, Boys Don't Cry), wants the same freedom every teenager craves. But when she can't have her way, her rebellious temperament erupts in violence.

title: The Berlin Affair
description: What begins as an innocent art class becomes a steamy triangle of erotic passions and forbidden love. A beautiful Japanese girl becomes the object of obsession in a devious relationship between the wife of a German diplomat and her husband.

title: The Commune
description: From Oscar®-nominated director Thomas Vinterberg (The Celebration, The Hunt), comes a funny and moving story of family and free love set in a freewheeling 1970s commune. Danish with English subtitles.

title: The Doll
description: When his girlfriend dumps him and moves out, Eddie and his friend Chris order a gorgeous model from an escort service named Natasha. But when she arrives, they boys begin to find something is unnaturally wrong with the model... possibly even deadly.

title: The First Time
description: At a summer resort, some teenage boys are drawn to a woman (Jacqueline Bisset) without a passport, whom they mistakenly identify as a prostitute. Under the imagined spell of her "allure," they help her cross the border.

title: The Gift
description: A woman with ESP is asked to help solve a mysterious murder.

title: The Hunted
description: Chasing their dream of landing their own hunting show, two hunters head into the dense, secluded mountains of West Virginia only to realize they are not alone.

title: The Lifeguard
description: Feeling unfilled, a 29 year old reporter quits her job in New York City and returns to her childhood home and the last time of happiness as a lifeguard, but takes this a bit too far when she starts a romantic relationship with a teenage boy.

title: The Shooter
description: A cowboy intervenes on behalf of a prostitute, who is being terrorized by a gang of thugs.

title: The Trip
description: Paul Groves, a television commercial director, is in the midst of a personality crisis. His wife Sally has left him and he seeks the help of his friend John, a self-styled guru who's an advocate of LSD.

title: To Keep The Light
description: Inspired by true stories, a lighthouse keeper's wife struggles with her work and her sanity as she cares for her sick husband in 19th century Maine.
